title: cinnamon breakfast cake(soul biscuits)
directions: Separate biscuits.
Melt margarine.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit in melted margarine, then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Overlap 15 biscuits around outer edge of 9-inch pan.
Overlap 5 biscuits to form inner circle.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar-cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: In large skillet, combine soup, honey, cornstarch, grated orange peel and nutmeg.
Over medium heat, cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add carrots.
Over low heat, cook 10 minutes or until vegetable is glazed, basting frequently.
Turn into serving bowl; garnish with raisins.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp with mushrooms and chicken
directions: Mix soups in pot with 1 1/2 cans of milk or milk and water; mix well until lumps are gone.
Add drained shrimp; mix well. Pour over rice and serve.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.

title: bourbon bons
directions: Cook at low heat for 3 hours.
Do not uncover.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: easy, elegant, foolproof chicken
directions: Mix soups, wine, rice and let stand several hours.
Arrange chicken breasts on top of mixture in ovenproof casserole.
Cover. Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, remove cover; stir gravy and bake for another hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nuria's russian salad
directions: Dice potatoes and boil until tender.
Boil eggs.
Drain potatoes.
Chop boiled eggs.
Combine potatoes, eggs, tuna, mayo and Italian dressing.
Finely chop 1/2 jar of olives and add. Form a mold on a medium platter and arrange rest of olives (whole) in an attractive pattern on top of mold.
Serve with crackers or vegetable salad, if desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in frying pan and drain off grease. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: butterscotch chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in morsels and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: cherry ice cream
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Pour in ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: Bake chicken in a covered dish at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Drain.
Combine tomatoes and cornstarch.
Stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Cook, stirring occasionally until thick.
Remove chicken from baking dish; pour sauce into dish, saving 1 cup sauce.
Arrange chicken over sauce.
Top with rest of sauce. Place 1 slice of cheese on each piece of chicken breast.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: rose d's "mushroom monterey"
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for about 2 minutes.
Add flour to sour cream; add cream mixture to mushrooms and heat just until it begins to boil.
Turn into a greased shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in frying pan; cook until meat is browned and onions tender. Arrange meat and corn in layers in a lightly greased casserole dish; season with salt and pepper. Cover with tomato soup. Spread mashed potatoes on top. Brush top with a beaten egg yolk and bake at 400° until potatoes are browned.

title: banana-nut bread(very moist)
directions: Mix well oil, sugar, eggs and salt.
Mix baking soda and buttermilk together.
Alternate adding flour and buttermilk mixture to your first mixture until all is used.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save the broth.
Bone chicken and place in bottom of a casserole dish (cutting the meat into smaller pieces, make the meat evenly distributed).
Over the chicken spread cream of chicken soup.
Mix well in a large bowl the stuffing mix, eggs, canned milk and onion.
Spread this over the chicken and chicken soup.
Over this pour the broth, at least 3 cups or more.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: At least 1 day before serving, mix mayo, sugar, vinegar and onion; refrigerate.
When ready to serve, chop broccoli, stems and all.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Mix well the broccoli, bacon and dressing.
Add raisins (optional).

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil together 2 to 3 minutes. Add 2 teaspoons baking soda to the mixture and cool. Add 3 cups flour and stir until well blended. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, sprayed with Pam and flour. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: wrapped brie
directions: Spray 1 sheet of phyllo with cooking spray.
Keep remaining pastry covered with a slightly damp towel to prevent it from drying out.
Place Brie in center of sheet.
Wrap phyllo around Brie. Repeat procedure 3 times, inverting Brie each time (turning cheese over), then set aside.
Layer remaining 4 sheets of pastry, spraying each with cooking spray.
Place wrapped Brie in center. Bring corners of phyllo to center of Brie to cover, gently gathering and pressing together in center to resemble a package. Carefully tie with string.
Coat wrapped Brie with cooking spray and place on a lightly greased baking sheet.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add 1 cup flour and 4 eggs. Beat well.
Add another cup of flour and 3 eggs; beat well.
Add another cup of flour and 3 more eggs.
Beat this well and add salt and pineapple.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Use a very large tube pan.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is bubbly and slightly brown.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Boil broccoli, potatoes and onion in water for 10 minutes. Drain.
Add seasons and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add milk, cream and butter.
Cook to boiling, but do not boil.
Mix water and flour.
Add to soup.
Cook until thickened.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Wash beans, trim ends and remove strings.
Put in vegetable steamer and place over boiling water.
Cover and steam 5 minutes. Drain and plunge into cold water.
Drain again.
Melt margarine in nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray.
Add mushrooms and garlic.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add beans, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Stir well and cook for 3 more minutes.

title: mushroom canapes
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg yolk, onion and salt in bowl.
Brown mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Add mushrooms to cream cheese mixture.
Cut rounds of bread about 2 inches in diameter.
Toast one side under broiler; butter untoasted side.
Heap cream cheese mixture on rounds.
Broil for a very few minutes, until they bubble and brown slightly.
Serve warm.

title: flo's taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and taco seasoning mix; add kidney beans. Drain.
In large container, mix lettuce, tomatoes, pepper and onions.
Add crushed chips, shredded cheese and warm hamburger mix just before serving.
Add Catalina dressing last.
(Hamburger mixture can be made early and heated before serving.)

title: chocolate chip cookie delight
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dip cookies in milk, one at a time, and hold for a few seconds.
Then place in dish.
Spread Cool Whip across layer of cookies.
Repeat these steps again to form a second layer.
Refrigerate before serving.
May garnish with additional chocolate chips.

title: petit cheese cakes
directions: Beat all except wafers together.
Beat until light and fluffy. Place 1 vanilla wafer cookie in bottom of cupcake paper cup. Fill 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling.
Makes 24 cupcakes.
Do not substitute low-fat cream cheese; filling will go flat.

title: mom's best baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients with bean broth; pour over beans.
Add meat. Bake at 300° until done, approximately 4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (don't overcook).
Cook rice as directed.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz together.
Then mix in the balance of the ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Heat at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Heat the first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish until butter is melted.
Drain the fruit. Place the fruit in the pan with the butter mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: cream corn chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1 cup kernel corn with the chicken broth.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes until corn is tender.
Puree in a food processor or blender.
Return the creamed corn to the saucepan together with the remaining cup of kernel corn, celery, hot pepper sauce, nutmeg and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes longer.
Stir in the light cream or milk.
Heat to the simmering point.
Serve hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: reuben delight
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Wash and drain sauerkraut and place in the baking dish evenly spread.
Cook noodles, drain well and spread evenly over sauerkraut.
Mix together soup, onions, mustard and milk.
Pour over noodles evenly.
Sprinkle cheese over noodles.
Crumble corn beef evenly over cheese.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and spread on top of corned beef. Bake at 250° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Take a fork and prick at 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine grahams, butter and cinnamon and press into pan.

title: spinach brownies(an hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
To flour mixture add eggs and melted butter.
Stir.
Add other ingredients and mix very well. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
May freeze and reheat for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain thoroughly.
Blend uncooked spinach with remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat.
Stir and cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Pour teriyaki sauce over meat and marinate for 1 hour.
Drain.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes on each side, preferably over charcoal.

title: baby's spoon hot rolls
directions: Mix warm water and yeast.
Melt butter and add sugar, egg and flour; add yeast mixture and mix with spoon.
Spoon into greased muffin pans and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: basic decorator's icing
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in mixer bowl and mix well.
Then add powdered sugar.

title: small sponge cake
directions: Measure flour and add baking powder and salt.
Sift.
Beat eggs hard and sift in sugar gradually.
Heat milk and add butter; stir into eggs.
Add flour mixture and flavoring.
Beat well. Bake in an ungreased tube pan for 30 or 40 minutes at 375°.
Allow to stand 1 hour.
Serve plain or frost.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: squash patties
directions: If too juicy, add more meal.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot grease.

title: sour cream dessert
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Stir in light cream and vanilla (mixture will look curdled, but will become smooth).
Stir is sour cream.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a 3 or 4-cup ring mold. Chill until firm; unmold.
Serve with fruit if desired.
Makes 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: quick shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil and cook onion, garlic, green pepper and celery, slowly about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce and water.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash, onion, pepper, pimento and salt.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Bring vinegar, sugar and mustard to a boil.
After squash has been in salt for 1 hour, drain and add to vinegar mixture. Bring to a second boil.
Place in jars and seal.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm and add to dry mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in rest of the flour to make stiff dough. Spoon into 2 loaf pans or 3 coffee cans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove from pans immediately and cool.
Slice and toast to serve with jam or honey.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and onion soup separately in bowl.
Drain juice from all but 1 can of green beans and add to soup mixture. Stir well.
Layer green bean mixture, potato chips, then Velveeta, green beans, potato chips, etc., ending with potato chips.
Cook in microwave oven for 25 minutes; take out and put Velveeta on top to melt.
In regular oven, cook at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Put Velveeta on top for last 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown turkey in skillet.
Add onion and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, taco seasoning, salt and pepper.
Simmer until liquid is gone.
Add cheese (reserve small amount).
Stir until cheese has melted.
In an 8 x 8-inch pan, layer meat mixture, then rice mixture.
Repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Measure and beat all ingredients, except nuts, at low speed until just mixed.
Increase speed to high and beat 8 minutes or until sugar is completely dissolved.
Fold in nuts and pour into 2 (9 x 9) pans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: greek chicken
directions: Melt butter and brown chicken; remove from pan.
Saute onion and garlic; add sauce, cinnamon, salt to taste and 1/2 teaspoon Cavender's.
Replace chicken and simmer covered until tender. Remove chicken; add a little water to sauce if too thick, then add 1 cup Minute rice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sourdough bread without starter
directions: Gently mix 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons instant potatoes, yeast and 1 cup of warm water. Allow a few minutes for yeast to dissolve before start timing. Place this mixture in a large mixing bowl. Leave mixture in 80° to 85° for 45 minutes. After the 45 minutes, make a stiff batter of yeast mixture, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup oil, 1 tablespoon salt, 1 1/2 cups warm water and 6 cups bread flour. Put this in a greased bowl and turn over so all sides will be greased. Cover with foil and let rise for about 2 hours or doubled in bulk. Punch down dough and divide into 3 parts. Knead each one on floured board. Place in 3 loaf pans and let rise about 2 more hours or until doubled in bulk. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°. When done, brush with butter and enjoy!!!

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter with chocolate.
Stir in flour and dash of salt. Add sugar.
Beat eggs and add to the ingredients.
Add vanilla. Pour into greased pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Cut
bread
into small cubes.
Add brown sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon
and
toss together in a shallow baking dish.
Alternate bread
cubes
and
apple
pie filling, ending with bread cubes. Pour melted butter or margarine evenly over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with cream or hard sauce.

title: ada's dumplings
directions: Place broth in large heavy Dutch oven.
Add cream of chicken soup and mix into broth until smooth.
Bring broth to a boil and add tortillas, cut in 2-inch squares.
Add 2 or 3 drops of yellow food coloring.
Turn heat on medium and cook, stirring often until thick.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Eat and enjoy.

title: apple tapioca
directions: *Fill 2-quart casserole 2/3 full of sliced, peeled and cored apples.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, then add the rest of the ingredients. Slice 4 or 5 golden and red Delicious apples and arrange around dip.

title: hungry jack cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then dip biscuits in melted margarine.
Put in dry ingredients and mix well.
Put in Bundt pan by standing biscuits on sides.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water until dissolved.
Fold in strawberries, bananas, pineapple and nuts. Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Keep rest of mixture at room temperature.
When firm, spread on sour cream and gently pour on rest of mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: angel food torte
directions: Slice angel food cake into 3 even layers.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Layer cake and Cool Whip mixture; top with cherry pie filling.
Repeat twice.
Ice top and sides with Cool Whip mixture; drizzle cherry pie filling on top and down sides.

title: peanut butter candy or cake icing
directions: Put sugar and milk in electric skillet on 260° and cook for 5 minutes. Turn off heat and add peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla; beat.
Pour onto buttered dish.
Let stand until firm, then top with pecan halves and cut in squares.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Butter 3-quart mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, soda, buttermilk and butter.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 30 to 40 minutes or until a soft ball forms in cold water; stir 2 to 3 times during cooking.
Add vanilla.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Cool until firm.
Store in tightly covered container in freezer no longer than 3 months or in refrigerator no longer than 1 1/2 months.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add vinegar and water; stir well and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool, add remaining ingredients.

title: aunt eunice's peanut brittle
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large saucepan.
Stir well and cook over medium heat until honey-colored (light).
Stir constantly.
Turn heat off and add scant teaspoon soda and mix real good.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix in order listed but not cheese.
Pour half of mixture into a hot greased pan (iron skillet).
Sprinkle half of cheese on this; add remaining mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This will make a 10 1/2-inch round skillet; don't make too thick.

title: peach cobbler
directions: *Note:
No sugar for canned in syrup peaches.

title: christmas gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 package strawberries (thawed), 1/2 the pineapple and 1 banana. Let chill.
Spread
with
layer
of
sour cream.
Repeat with remaining ingredients and put on top of sour cream; chill.

title: pizza
directions: Buy several pizzas from St. Paul's Sr. High U.M.Y.F. at their annual pizza sale.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pizza directly on rack until done.
Eat heartily and take joy in the fact that you have had a good pizza and have helped the youth of our congregation.

title: crock-pot cube steak
directions: Pour 1 can of each soup into crock-pot.
Place steak on top of soup.
Pour remaining 2 cans of soup on top of steak.
Cook on low heat all day.
Recipe can be divided.

title: polka dot party roll
directions: Prepare angel food batter as directed on package.
Spread half of batter in a greased, wax paper-lined jellyroll pan.
(Use remaining batter for cupcakes.)
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes; cool.
Add vanilla to whipped cream; reserve 1 cup.
Fold 2 cups marshmallows into remaining whipped cream; spread on jellyroll and roll up.
Top with whipped cream; sprinkle with marshmallows.
Chill several hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Reserve 3 tablespoons for topping. Press remainder on bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: whole grain jam squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves in large mixing bowl; beat at low speed on electric mixer until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 2 cups mixture; press remaining onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread preserves evenly over base.
Sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake in preheated hot oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: osso buco
directions: Wipe the veal shanks with damp towels.
Combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Rub into veal shanks, coating them well on all sides.
Slowly heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add veal shanks, 3 at a time, and brown well on all sides, 30 minutes in all.
Remove as browned.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce, thoroughly and shape into small balls.
Put in open roasting pan and pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy party cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's (reserve the rest for decoration). Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with rest of candy.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: date cookies
directions: Cook dates, salt, sugar, water and lemon juice until thick; add nuts.
Cream butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Chill in fridge 1/2 hour.
Divide in 3 parts. Roll out to 1/4-inch rectangle.
Spread thin layer of date mix. Roll up like a jelly roll and chill until firm enough to slice. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pizza surprise(appetizer)
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo and cream cheese together.
Spread on flat dish to form a round base.
Add shrimp cocktail sauce, then shrimp.
Add
cheese,
then onion tops or green peppers. Last, add tomatoes.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate cherry cookie
directions: Drain cherries and set aside (save the juice).
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients. Form 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Press cherry into center.
Set aside.

title: quick cheesecake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust; spoon cherry pie filling over pie.
(May substitute your favorite fruit filling for topping.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Garnish and serve with crackers, chips, vegetables, etc.

title: fruit mix dessert
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add to top of pie and bake at 325° about 15 minutes or until brown.
Remove and let cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in small amount of salted water with onion and celery for 45 minutes.
Cool in stock.
When cool, skin and debone.
Cook broccoli in salted water until tender-crisp. Layer broccoli in bottom of buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Put chicken breasts on broccoli spears.
Mix undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and top with buttered crumbs or stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: onion celeste
directions: Cook onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Put in casserole dish.
Add milk and soup.
Put cheese on top and stir lightly.
Arrange bread on top and bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: hot cherry pudding
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl except eggs; beat at low speed until mixed (a thick batter); last add eggs and mix well.
Fold in fresh cherries.
(Also good made with fresh peaches, black raspberries, blackberries or blueberries).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with milk or cream.

title: soy pork balls
directions: Mix sausage and bread crumbs well.
Shape into small balls. In hot skillet, brown balls; remove and add sugar, mustard, soy sauce and water.
Return balls and bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until liquid is gone.

title: chowlupa(chicken casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
*If using corn tortillas, cut them in strips and layer with chicken in pan.
If you are using corn chips, crush them and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, green chiles and onion in bowl; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture and chips, if using them.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch crispies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in double boiler. When melted and smooth, remove from heat and stir in corn flakes. Drop onto waxed paper in teaspoon amounts.
Cool until firm and cool.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Slice zucchini thin.
Slice onions fine.
Cover with water. Add salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 2 hours again.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Pack immediately (very hot) in sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 3 pints.

title: egg and sausage bake(microwave)
directions: Crumble sausage into 2-quart casserole.
Add green pepper and onion.
Microwave at High 3 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Break sausage into small pieces; drain well.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Beat egg, milk, salt and pepper in 2-quart casserole.
Reduce power to 50%.
Microwave 5 to 9 minutes or until eggs are set but still very moist, stirring every 2 minutes.
Pour eggs over sausage.
Sprinkle cheeses
over eggs.
Cover with wax paper.
Place an inverted saucer in oven. Microwave at 50% until center is set (10 to 12 minutes) but slightly moist on top, rotating 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.

title: a tasty pot roast
directions: Brown roast on	all
sides in oil in a Dutch oven.
Add seasonings,
onion, cranberry sauce, water and apples.
Simmer 1 1/2
to
2 hours.
Remove meat from pan.
Combine cornstarch and vinegar.
Stir into liquid in pan.	Heat to boiling.
Stir until thickened.	Serve with noodles or rice.

title: golden peach crunch
directions: Drain peaches thoroughly.
Mix cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice and turn into baking dish.
Combine oats, butter, sugar and salt.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° approximately 30 minutes.

title: fabulous punch
directions: Dissolve sugar with the hot water, then add Kool-Aid and mix until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale last, mixing very slowly.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Heat in saucepan over low heat.
Serve warm.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour throughly.
Add cocoa and mix. Add 1/4 cup of milk and mix.
Add eggs and remaining 1 3/4 cups milk.
Mix well.
Cook in microwave for about 10 minutes.
Stir several times until thick.
After cooking add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into crust.

title: polenta
directions: Bring salted water to a boil. Sprinkle corn meal very slowly and stir continuously until thickens, about 20 minutes.
Pour in large platter or individual serving plates. Top with favorite tomato sauce and grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Butter a Bundt cake pan and sprinkle with sugar before pouring mixture in pan.
Bake for 55 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing.
This is easy and everyone loves it!

title: caramel squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 16 x 10-inch pan. Combine caramels and 1/3 cup Pet milk in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until all caramels are melted (keep warm).

title: frosty date balls
directions: Cream margarine and 1/3 cup confectioners sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in dates and pecans.
Shape into thirty 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased 10 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Roll warm date balls in 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Yield:
30 servings.

title: green beans almandine
directions: Cook green beans in salted boiling water in a small covered saucepan, separating beans with a fork, for 8 minutes, until crisp-tender.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: blueberry muffins(yield:  12)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: kolachy
directions: Put butter in bowl of electric mixer.
Beat on medium speed until butter is fluffy.
Add cream cheese, beat until well incorporated.
Beat in flour, sugar, and salt until most of flour is mixed.
Finish mixing by hand. (Do not overbeat or kolachy will be tough.)
Flatten dough into a disk; wrap in plastic wrap. Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place slices of cabbage in bottom of large skillet or cooker. Add a layer of sliced potatoes.
Next add a layer of wieners, cut in 3 pieces.
Melt a stick of butter and pour over layers.
Cook until done.
You might need to add a little water.

title: lasagne
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, eggs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. In a lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour sauce (1/2 cup) on bottom and spread evenly.
Place first layer of noodles on top. Spread a heavy layer of sauce and meat.
On top of this, spread evenly part of the Ricotta cheese mixture.
Place a layer of Scamorze cheese.
Now, repeat these layers until the top.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together ingredients until smooth.
Beat in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients; adding half & half to fill line of your ice cream maker. Stir and freeze. Makes 1 gallon of Ice Cream.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chops in baking pan.
Salt chops and top with lemon slice (can use juice, also).
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Pour 1 tablespoon of catsup on each.
Bake 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.

title: chuck roast
directions: Stuff roast with crushed garlic, salt and black and red pepper. Plenty of salt on outside (this makes it brown nicely). Marinate overnight in a baking plastic bag with soy sauce.
Take out of plastic bag.
Brown on all sides in an iron pot (no flour). Cover and cook on low heat 3 to 4 hours.
Take out roast and thicken gravy with a little flour.
Soy sauce mixture can be frozen and used over in the plastic bag.

title: korean chicken marinade
directions: Dip each piece of chicken in marinade and let stand 30 minutes. Bake at 300° to 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients through blend in a large bowl with Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: master zucchini medley
directions: Parboil potatoes 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Reserve.
Saute first 5 ingredients in oil for 3 or 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, oregano, garlic salt/powder, black pepper and cook over medium to low for no more than 5 or 6 minutes.
Delicious whole meal served with cornbread.
Lock the door, take the phone off the hook and turn off television cause you won't want to be disturbed once you start eatin'.

title: poppy seed dressing for fresh fruit salad
directions: Blend all ingredients (except poppy seed) in blender. Stir in seed. Keeps 2 to 3 months.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and Grape-Nuts.
Add butter.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Add milk slowly; mix thoroughly.
Pour into well buttered baking dish; bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serve warm or cold with whipped topping.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Combine white sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Shake to mix. Place one biscuit at a time in sugar mixture and shake.
Place or pile in well-greased Bundt pan or tube pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with crumbled meat and top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over cheese.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix 2
tablespoons
of
the flour and the ginger.
Coat pork with
the
flour mixture.
Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet. Fry pork until
brown; remove from skillet.

title: quiche a la jack
directions: Measure 1 cup of cheese and layer on bottom of pie shell. Layer bacon and onion on top of cheese.
Layer the remaining 2 cups of cheese on top.
Beat eggs and pepper.
Add half and half and mustard.
Pour this mixture over the layered ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: mona's ice cream dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, saving some crumbs for top.
Slice or spoon ice cream and layer it on top; as it softens, spread around so it's even.
Top with crumbs.
Freeze.
Cut into individual servings.

title: tid bits
directions: Mix and shape.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into small dices.
Parboil until soft. Drain.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix vinegar and milk together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pie pan.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. (I like to use iron skillet.)	Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Sift flour with baking powder; add alternately with milk to sugar mixture. Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites with salt.
Fold into batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 beaten egg.
Press mixture evenly on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pan and bake at 350° until brown. Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream, Miracle Whip and Hidden Valley Ranch until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust and top with diced onions, green pepper and tomatoes.
Add shredded cheese, bacon bits, olives and fresh mushrooms if desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: baked pasta
directions: Cook bowtie pasta until al dente.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 25 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl slightly beat eggs.
Stir in corn syrup, brown sugar, melted butter and salt.
Add pecans and vanilla to mixture.
Pour into a deep dish Pet-Ritz pie crust shell.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet at 375° until center is set when gently shaken, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: chili rellenos squares
directions: Layer cheese and chilies in a lightly greased, 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour eggs over top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sausage and corn cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add liquid and eggs, then add sausage and corn.
Fry on hot griddle like pancakes (using some sausage drippings).
Serve with country gravy and fresh fruit salad (if desired).

title: swiss almond chicken
directions: In frying pan, saute onion, celery and chicken in oil until chicken is golden and celery and onions are clear.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and put into iron skillet.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies; place in 9 x 13 pan, sticky side up.
Slice bananas over Twinkies.
Mix pudding with milk.
When thick, add pineapple.
Spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: summer marmalade
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook at a slow boil about 1/2 hour.
When thick and clear, it's done.
Seal in sterilized jam jars.
(Do this when jam is hot and invert the jar.) It will keep indefinitely.
Makes 4 to 5 small jars.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts into sour cream to coat, then coat with crushed Ritz crackers.
Lay in pan and dribble the melted butter over the top.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and swiss buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
On floured surface, separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Gently pinch perforations together on each rectangle.
Roll each into a 7 x 5-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham and cheese on dough, leaving 1/2-inch rim of dough all around.
Spread mustard on each one.
Brush rim of dough with egg.
Fold dough and filling over so the 5-inch sides meet.
Seal edges.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes until brown.
Serves 4.

title: country chicken vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broth and rice.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add mixed vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: berry cider fizz
directions: Place raspberries with syrup in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Strain raspberry puree; discard seeds. Combine puree and remaining ingredients in large pitcher.

title: fresca cranberry jello
directions: Mix together and pour into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: white grape juice tea
directions: Place all ingredients in gallon jar and finish filling jar with water.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low overnight.

title: oven home fries
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray small rimmed cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Scrub 2 medium size baking potatoes (about 6 ounces each); cut each into 8 lengthwise wedges.
Arrange wedges in single layer on prepared cookie sheet.
Spray lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon each salt and black pepper.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, turning wedges over halfway through cooking time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: In a blender, put mustard, vinegar, catsup, lemon juice and oil, then add onions, celery, Tabasco and salt; blend.
Boil shrimp; peel and mix with blended ingredients.
Marinate at least 24 hours.
Serve as party food using toothpicks or as an appetizer on shredded lettuce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together. Add sifted dry ingredients. Cover and chill at least 1 hour. Roll out 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth or board. Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.

title: apple-pecan coffee cake
directions: Prepare topping.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixer bowl.
Add sugar, salt, nondairy milk, shortening and 1 1/4 cups of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in remaining flour; continue stirring until smooth.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls onto topping in pan. Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge pudding cake
directions: Cream butter (or margarine) and sugar.
Add vanilla and chocolate and mix until well blended.
Add all flour and baking powder, then all milk to chocolate mixture.
Mix well (add nuts). Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.

title: peanut butter rice krispie bars
directions: Heat Karo syrup and sugar in large bowl in microwave until bubbly and rolling in bowl (about 5 minutes).
Add peanut butter and stir until creamy.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Press into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and use to frost bars.
Store in airtight container.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Separate chicken wing at joint.
Cut off tip.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Drain chicken.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain the meat; add taco seasoning and simmer according to package directions.
Stir in sour cream and corn. Pour the mixture into a casserole dish.
Pour the cornbread mixture on top.
Bake according to the cornbread directions until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve with sides of salsa.

title: mini peanut butter cheese cakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 12 medium muffin tin cups with paper liners.
Place a wafer in each cup.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in a medium bowl until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Top with mini Reese's cup and bake 15 minutes.

title: cucumber mayonnaise for fish
directions: Mix and chill thoroughly.
Makes a wonderful tartar sauce.

title: raspberry brownies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and chocolate; mixing well.
Add flour to butter mixture, mixing well; stir in walnuts.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler; set aside.
Mix 2/3 cup evaporated milk and softened margarine in cake mix.
Pour half into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out.

title: lemon cake with lemon jello
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add the eggs one at a time. Beat well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When baked, pierce top with fork and put on topping while cake is still warm.

title: italian broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli 5 to 7 minutes.
Combine eggs, soup, oregano, tomatoes and broccoli in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening and white sugar.
Add applesauce; mix in raisins and nuts.
Add dry ingredients, mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it tests done.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook onions in a very small amount of water for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add frozen broccoli, salt and a very little pepper. Cook until thawed.
Add Velveeta cheese cut into chunks and stir until melted.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
If using frozen beans, cook and drain; canned beans, drain.
In medium bowl, combine beans, milk, soup, salt, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Layer 1/3 of tortilla on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (can be torn to pieces). Brown meat.
Drain. Add enchilada sauce and cream of chicken.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour 1/3 of mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle 1/3 of cheese over meat mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream or plain yogurt.

title: oatcakes
directions: Rub lard into flour and oatmeal.
Sift in sugar, salt and powders.
Add beaten egg and make into a nice dough with hot water.
Roll out thin and cut into cakes.
Bake in a hot oven for a few minutes.

title: post office cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs; mix with creamed mixture. Add flour and almond extract.
Mix altogether.
Place on a greased jelly roll pan.
Pat out.
Score top into squares.
Put 1 teaspoon of pie filling on each square.
Bake.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Dust with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: frozen date salad
directions: Cream together the mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, dates and pecans; stir well.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour into shallow casserole dish.
Freeze and cut into squares. Can be served on a bed of lettuce or served as a dessert.

title: swedish cabbage rolls(serves 6)
directions: Boil cabbage leaves for 3 minutes; drain.
Combine egg, milk, onion, pepper, salt, ground beef and cooked rice.
Wrap mixture in boiled cabbage leaves tightly.
Place in a slow pot.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover.
Cook for 7 hours.

title: lucy marse's hush puppy recipe
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add 1 egg, green onions and enough milk to mix a stiff dough.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into hot grease.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup cookies and the "rocks" into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk and add lemon juice. Freeze for
1 hour or until thick.
Fold in whipped cream and freeze in 2 ice trays. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish.

title: taco soup
directions: In skillet, chop onion over ground meat; brown and drain.
Put in large pot, adding tomato sauce, canned tomatoes, drained corn, pintos, green chilies, taco seasoning and Hidden Valley mix.
Add enough water for soup consistency and simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, beat well and add hot water.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tantalizing thai soup
directions: Saute shallots, garlic, and ginger in a small amount of vegetable oil, just until fragrant.
Add the mushrooms and saute about 30 seconds.
Add broth, lime leaves, lemon grass, galangal root, fish sauce, soy sauce, and lime juice.
Stir thoroughly and bring to a boil over medium-low heat.
Blend in the coconut milk and chilli paste; bring to a boil again then simmer for 2 minutes over low heat. Garnish with cilantro before serving.
Season with more fresh lime juice to your liking.This soup is guaranteed to have you chasing after the very last drop!

title: favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, soda and baking powder; mix well.
Add rolled oats and stir.
Add nuts and chocolate chips; mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hermits(passover)
directions: Stir coffee into cake mix in mixing bowl.
Break egg into measuring cup; add oil.
Add water to make 1/2 cup.
Add egg mixture to bowl with cake mix and beat at high speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Fold in raisins or currants and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.
They will be soft, so cool on sheets 1 minute before moving them to cooling racks.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: scones
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; then cut butter until crumbly.
Stir in egg and milk; dough will be sticky.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: nacho dip
directions: Finish with a layer of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve as a dip for nacho chips.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Heat 1 inch of vegetable oil in a deep skillet.
Use a funnel; cover bottom of funnel with finger.
Fill with batter; release batter in circular motion.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Can be served with syrup.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour, liquids, salt and pepper.
Allow to come to boil.
Add chicken and pour into casserole.
Top with frozen pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Use casserole dish about the size of pie crust so that meat will be covered.

title: special occasion rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar.
Stir and cool.
Dissolve yeast in water and add to milk.
Add 1/2 of flour; stir well.
Add egg and salad oil; stir.
Add rest of flour; knead on floured board until smooth.
May be put in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.
Let rise once.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brown and serve rolls.

title: dave's potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except eggs.
Taste for flavor, adding more mayonnaise or mustard, if needed.
Add 2 dozen hard-boiled eggs, chopped. Slice the other eggs and garnish the top.
Refrigerate.
Makes enough for a large family gathering.

title: fried apple rings
directions: Core the apples.
Cut into 1/2-inch rings.
Saute the rings in margarine until just tender.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover pan. Cook a few minutes more until they are glazed and golden.

title: pear relish
directions: Put ground pears, onions, pepper, celery seed, sugar, vinegar and salt in large pot.
Add spice that has been put into cloth. Cook from 15 to 20 minutes.
Put into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs thoroughly.	Add margarine, coconut, buttermilk and vanilla in
that
order.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (deep dish) and bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread rhubarb in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle sugar and dry jello mix over rhubarb.
Spread marshmallows evenly over rhubarb, sugar and jello.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Spread batter evenly over ingredients in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Garnish each portion with a dollop of whipped topping.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in large saucepan.
Add milk and butter and mix.
Cook on top of stove and boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Mix well, then drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix together; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Put the cranberries, oranges and apples through a food chopper.
Mix all ingredients together and store in the refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, egg, onion, crumbs, flakes, salt and 1/4 cup soup mix.
Shape into balls.
Brown in shortening.
Pour remaining soup in and simmer 30 minutes.

title: mock veal cutlets
directions: Mix together and form into patties.
Brown on both sides in frying pan.
Remove from pan and place in bottom of casserole. Add one can cream of mushroom soup over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Place milk in double boiler and add flour.
Stir until smooth; cook over low heat until thick like custard.
Remove and cool well.
Beat shortening until creamy and gradually add sugar and beat until smooth.
Then add cooled milk mixture and vanilla and beat until creamy smooth.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream shortening with sugars. Add peanut butter, 1/2 tsp. vanilla, egg and 1/4 c. milk. Sift in flour, baking soda, and salt. Add oatmeal; mix well. Spread mixture into a 13X9 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes, cool thoroughly. Combine 2 c. powdered sugar with cocoa. 3 Tbsp. melted butter, boiling water and remaining vanilla. Mix will. Spread frosting mixture over cooled bars in pan. Heat remaining butter in saucepan until brown. Stir in remaining powdered sugar and enough remaining milk to make drizzling consistency. Drizzle glaze over frosting.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a glass bowl.
Sprinkle crushed graham crackers over bottom and sides of bowl.
Dissolve marshmallows in milk on top of the stove.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Add drained pineapple and fruit cocktail to the cooled milk mixture.
Then add whipped cream and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: creeping cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in dish.
Mix sugar, milk, flour and baking powder to make batter.
Pour batter over oleo, then add fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 3/4 cup white sugar.
Roll biscuits in cinnamon-sugar mix.
Drop rolled pieces in greased Bundt pan layering in chopped pecans.
Bring to boil the 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, vanilla, 1 cup white sugar, water and oleo. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes; cool.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and brown sugar together. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Add oats and nuts. Mix well. Shape into quarter size balls and drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take off of fire.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; then add oats and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly oil a 2-quart casserole.
Heat the olive oil in a skillet and add the onion, garlic, celery and mushrooms.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
Transfer to a casserole and add the tomatoes, rice, salt and pepper.
Pour in the broth, stir, cover and bake 30 minutes. Stir again and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Sprinkle cranberries with 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside. Sift remaining sugar, flour, baking powder and salt into large mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, beat the egg, milk and oil.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Do not overmix. Add berries and lemon peel.
Bake in muffin cups or loaf pan (6 x 11-inch) for 18 to 22 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage very fine and pour a little boiling water over it.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cabbage and apples to bacon fat.
Add a little more boiling water to mixture.
Simmer until tender.
Sprinkle with flour, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add milk, eggs and oil, stirring well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and shake! To serve, fill cup 1/2 full of mix and add boiling water. You can fill Mason jars and give as gifts.

title: chocolate peanut butter cup smoothie
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend at high speed until smooth.
Serve immediately, topped with scoops of frozen yogurt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Cover with 2 cups corn flakes, crushed and mixed with 1/4 stick oleo.
Bake at 350°.

title: mallets
directions: Cut wieners into thirds and repeat with bacon. Wrap bacon pieces around wieners and secure with toothpick.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix jelly and mustard well.
Drizzle over mallets. Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes, covered, at 375°.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more until bacon crisps.

title: fry delight
directions: Bake
fries at 350°F until lightly crisp.
Fry onions until lightly brown and add
fries, salt, pepper, seasoned salt, lemon pepper, Vegeta and vinegar.
Fry on medium heat for 7 minutes.
Remove and place on plate.
Place oranges on outside rim of plate.
Add tomatoes in the center of plate and sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Wash the grapes and dry well.
Beat egg white until slightly frothy.
Sprinkle it over the grapes.
Dust with sugar and let dry.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat. After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces. Store in airtight container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, seasonings and bouillon.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring well until blended.
Gradually add flour mixture to hot vegetables, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Add Velveeta.
Stir until melted.

title: three bean salad
directions: In a large bowl mix together the beans, green pepper and onion.
Set aside.
Mix together the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over the vegetables.
Prepare the day before serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine 2 cups of sugar, hot water, tea and cold water.
Add pineapple juice, grapefruit juice, orange juice, lemon juice and ginger ale.
Add fruit and more sugar to taste.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients and drain in colander.
Add pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse in cold water and drain.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 2-inch square pieces.
Saute garlic and onion in shortening; remove from skillet.
Dredge beef in mixture of flour, salt and pepper; brown evenly over low heat.
Return onion and garlic to skillet.
Add mushrooms, catsup and bouillon.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Add additional bouillon if needed.
Add sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Serve over rice or noodles sprinkled with poppy seed.

title: meacham's best potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, dill weed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onions and celery.
Mix lightly.
Chill.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt oleo, beat eggs.
Break bread in small pieces.
Add melted oleo, sugar, pineapple, eggs, marshmallows.
Put in greased casserole and pour the milk over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour.
Very good with baked ham.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a pie crust.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until set, about 30 minutes or less.

title: cheese salad
directions: Grind together. Add 1 cup pickle juice or more until mixture is moist. Can be frozen. You can add a little mayonnaise when taken from freezer if you like.

title: classic rice salad
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with tomatoes and ripe olives.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Bake in tube cake pan.

title: coconut pie filling(diabetic, sugar-free)
directions: Soak coconut in milk and add next 4 ingredients.
Cook until filling begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter or margarine.
Cool; pour into baked pie crust.
Top with either Cool Whip, whipped cream or meringue.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Toss cheeses together.
Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients except tortilla chips and cheese.
Layer in order: 1/2 chips, 1/2 sauce, 1/2 cheeses.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: deer roast
directions: Put deer roast in slow cooker/crock-pot.
Salt and pepper roast and put 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce on meat.
Mix soup mix by directions on pack; pour over meat.
Add all other ingredients and cook slow for 3 hours.

title: pineapple-cranberry squares
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until sauce has melted.
Add undrained pineapple.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cool and refrigerate.
Spread Cool Whip over top and add chopped nuts.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop batter by spoonful in hot grease. Cook until brown on all sides.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.

title: rocky road clusters
directions: Place chocolate in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate melts, stirring occasionally.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl; add chocolate, mixing well.

title: quickie strawberry jam
directions: Wash and hull the strawberries and slice or crush them into a saucepan.
Add the water and jello, then cook, stirring, over a moderate heat until the mixture boils.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Allow to cool, then pour into 3 small jars.
Refrigerate or freeze.
There are 3 calories per tablespoon.

title: grandma audrey's rice
directions: Heat butter in a skillet.
Add the onion and garlic and saute until onion is done (transparent).
Add the rice and saute until rice is just turning light brown.
Add the bouillon and cover tightly.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
You may add soy sauce to the bouillon if you want a more intense flavor.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix as plain cake and bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°. (Smaller loaves take less time.)
Fill pans 2/3 full.

title: judy's easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in pan cobbler is to cook in.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Pour over butter. Pour in canned fruit with juice, no need to stir.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar over top of cobbler mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: easy brown bread
directions: Mix all together in bowl with spoon.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Pan need not be greased, but invert pan on rack when done to let steam loosen it.

title: chicken with cheese
directions: Place chicken between Handi-Wrap and pound thin.
Roll in flour, dip in milk, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry chicken in a pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Saute onion in pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Blend in flour. Stir in cream, salt and pepper.
You may add more cream.
Add cheese; cook on low heat until melted.
May need to thin sauce down a little more.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in thin round slices, also onions. Place in gallon bowl or container and sprinkle with salt. Cover with ice cubes. Let stand 3 hours. Stir once or twice. (Drain and add more ice.) Rinse and drain. Bring spices, sugar, vinegar and water to a boil. Add onions and cucumbers. Simmer. When hot, pack in hot jars and seal.

title: died and gone to heaven cake
directions: Bake white cake according to directions. Poke full of holes with a fork while hot. Pour the Eagle Brand milk and then the cream of coconut over it. When completely cool, frost with Cool Whip and top with coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: chili pie
directions: Put 1 cup chips into a bowl.
Pour heated chili over chips. Sprinkle onions and peppers on; then pour cheese sauce over top. Makes 3 servings.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine all ingredients and work dough (knead).
Let rise. Roll out. Deep fry in hot oil.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Melt 1/2 cup sugar in a large saucepan, stirring constantly. Put milk and the remaining sugar in another saucepan and heat on low until it comes to a boil. Do not boil.
Put the two pans to cook at the same time and they should be ready in 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour milk and sugar into pan of melted sugar (it will be brown), stirring constantly (it will bubble up really big).
Add nuts immediately while still stirring. Cook to soft ball stage in water. Add vanilla and butter. Beat until creamy.
Drop patties on wax paper to cool.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix until no lumps remain.
Divide remaining ingredients in half; place in each of the pie shells.
Pour milk and egg mixture equally into each pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until knife comes out clean, or until top is golden brown.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water with soda over the dates; let stand 1/2 hour.
Add shortening, sugar, flour, vanilla, egg and nuts; mix well.
Put into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken caribbean
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook chicken until browned on all sides.
In cup, combine remaining ingredients. Pour mixture over chicken and heat to boiling.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon into skillet with 1-inch hot grease. Fry on each side.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight (covered).
Stir before serving.

title: fifth avenue cake(quick and easy cake dessert)
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Make pudding according to directions on box.
Pour over angel food cake. Spread Cool Whip over top of pudding.
Crumble up candy bars and sprinkle over top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for about 4 hours before cutting.
Use a regular 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: zesty cheese spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, salad dressing, sugar and lemon juice.
Add green pepper, pimento and onion and mix well.
Serve as a vegetable dip or spread on crackers.

title: chocolate almond coffee
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Pour in boiling water.
Stir.
Add cream and almond extract.
Serve hot.

title: fruit and nut bars
directions: In a small bowl, mix wafer crumbs and butter. Press into 9x13 inch pan. Layer with pecans and cherries. Pour milk over top, and allow to set about 10 minutes. Bake 24 minutes at 350°. Cut while warm. Makes 24 bars.

title: sweet cream pound cake
directions: All ingredients at room temperature.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat egg and add milk. Sift dry ingredients together, then add to milk and egg mixture. Beat until fluffy. Pour into funnel. Pour this into hot fat (oil), about 375°. Keep finger over funnel and let out a little batter at a time. As you drop the batter in oil, swirl around in skillet until brown and turn once. Serve with confectioners sugar and syrup.

title: chicken little fingers
directions: Chicken Little Fingers, strips of chicken baked in a coating of bread crumbs and sesame seed, are served with a tangy plum sauce.

title: blonde cookie bars
directions: Soften margarine. Add sugar, brown sugar and egg. Cream together. Add vanilla, flour, nuts and chips. Put into baking dish. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican fiesta turkey wings
directions: Rinse turkey.
Cut wings into 2 pieces.
Place in skillet with water.
Bring to a boil; turn down heat.
Cover.
Simmer 2 hours. Pour off liquid.
Combine tomato sauce and taco mix in small bowl; pour over turkey.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and heat 3 to 5 minutes more or until cheese melts. Makes 4 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cover with ice water and chill one hour.
Drain.
Break flowerets into smaller pieces.
Add dressing and let stand 2 hours.
Just before serving add avocado, olives, tomatoes and cheese.
Toss lightly.
Serve on crisp greens. Serves 8.

title: crab supreme
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients well. Spread on a shallow platter. Spread chili sauce over cheese mixture. Spread crab meat over chili sauce. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: ham quiche
directions: Brown ham, garlic and onion in olive oil until lightly browned.
Mix and beat eggs.
Add half and half and condiments. Put ham mixture in bottom of lightly browned pie crust.
Then, pour creamy mixture over ham mixture.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top of mixture.
Cover edge of pie crust with foil; place on cookie sheet and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rotini lasagna
directions: Add salt, pepper, parsley and grated cheese to Ricotta cheese. Mix until blended.
Lay rotini on bottom of casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cup sauce, 1/2 Ricotta mixture, layer additional ziti, Ricotta and sauce.
Add Mozzarella cheese to top.
Bake in 375° oven for 3/4 hour, covered.
Uncover and bake additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grill-side garden salad
directions: *One
cup cooked, fresh corn kernels or 1 (8 3/4 ounce) can whole kernel corn, drained, may be substituted.

title: no crust chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a blender (or mixer can be used) and blend on high for one minute.
Pour mixture into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Cool completely before serving.
If desired top with whipped cream.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix with spoon sugars, flour and oil.
Remove 1/2 cup and set aside for topping.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle crumbs and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple sage tea
directions: Steep bags of tea in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add honey and pineapple sage.
Let steep for 15 minutes. Strain and pour into glasses.

title: nachos
directions: Put cheese
on chips.
Place on baking sheet.
Top each with an olive slice.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: zucchini bread #2
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
In a separate mixing bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add dry mixture to sugar mixture in large bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add shredded zucchini, nuts and raisins if desired.
Makes 2 loaves.
Pour into bread pans and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Be sure to grease and flour pans.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as per instructions on package; drain well.
Add margarine and 1 1/2 cups of grated cheese.
Let cheese and margarine melt.
Add cottage cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Put remaining grated cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
In a small bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with seasoned flour (use all the flour). In a large skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serve with potatoes or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs gently for 10 minutes.
Cool eggs, peel and wash. Cut eggs in halves lengthways.
Slip out yolks mashed with fork. Mix in salt, pepper, prepared mustard, sweet relish and salad dressing.
Refill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up lightly.
Chopped pimentos may be added, if desired.

title: sourdough french bread
directions: Sprinkle
sugar
and yeast over 1/4 cup water.	Let sit until it	doubles.
Place
1 cup hot water in food processor; add oil, salt and 2 cups flour.
Pulse.
Add 2 cups flour and pulse to combine well.
Add flour (up to 1 cup) while continuously running;
process
to
knead
(approximately 1 to 1 1/2 minutes). Place in oiled bowl.
Let rise until doubled (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down; form into loaves and let rise.
Heat oven to	400°.
Bake for
minutes;
reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until done and nicely brown.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: manicotti
directions: Seasonings:
Use pepper, onion powder, garlic powder, small amount of thyme, oregano, marjoram and parsley.

title: popsicles that don't melt
directions: Dissolve 1 package of flavored gelatin in 1 cup hot water. Add 1 cup sugar to small package unsweetened Kool-Aid, the same flavor as gelatin, and 2 cups cold water.
Pour into molds and freeze.

title: elegant rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sour cream and almonds, in large mixing bowl.
Stir in 2 cups water.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 2 hours, or until rice is tender and moisture is absorbed.
Add additional water, if needed. Stir in sour cream; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: festive cranapple punch
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring 1 1/2 quarts water to boil. Dissolve sugar in water; set aside to cool.
To make tea: Use 2 tea bags and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate all ingredients.
Just before serving, mix ingredients in a large bowl (punch bowl).
Makes about sixteen 1-cup servings.
This recipe can easily be doubled.

title: easy congealed salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Combine all in one dish and mix well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: my best pot pie
directions: Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, onion, soup broth, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add water and milk stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute while stirring.
Stir in chicken and set aside.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and add 2 pats butter.
Sprinkle cheese if desired.
Bake 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar, beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir baking soda with milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Then add oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: italian beef for a crowd
directions: Add all ingredients in slow cooker. Cook for 6 hours, shredding beef with a fork intermittently.

title: microwave chocolate cake
directions: Spray
a
9-inch round microwave-safe dish with cooking spray. Combine
mix, eggs, mayonnaise and milk in bowl.
Pour into prepared
dish.
Microwave
at
half
power
(50% ) for 7 minutes, turning
once.
Turn
again.
Microwave at full power (100%) for 2 or 3 minutes or until cake tester inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Remove to rack to cool completely. Makes 8 servings.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper chicken. Brown in melted margarine. Remove chicken breasts and place in Pyrex casserole (9 x 13-inches). Thicken margarine (that was used to brown chicken) with the flour. Add wine and mushroom soup to the mixture. Place onions and mushrooms around chicken; pour soup mixture over it. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve over rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop 1 teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon into bowl, removing any skin and bones. Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly. Spoon into loaf pan, greased with nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple junk
directions: Cream butter, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add pineapple.
Fold in bread crumbs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Beat cheese.
Add milk while mixing, blend well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice; blend well.
Pour into shell.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: leftover potato cakes
directions: *To taste or use your favorite spices.

title: aunt edith's chocolate (no egg) cake
directions: Blend ingredients in large mixer bowl.
In separate small bowl, mix 2 teaspoons baking soda and 2 teaspoons vinegar until soda dissolves.
Add to cake batter and beat well for 2 to 3 minutes. Bake in greased and floured pans for approximately 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: roast chicken with vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine oil, lemon juice, salt, thyme, rosemary and marjoram.
Set aside.
Remove fat from chicken cavity opening.
Place garlic in cavity.
Set chicken in 10 x 15-inch roasting pan.
Brush chicken with oil mixture.
Arrange potatoes and onions in pan around chicken.
Roast for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add peas to vegetables, stirring to turn potatoes and onion pieces.
Roast 30 to 40 minutes longer, basting chicken once or twice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate treats
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and baking soda.
Stir into creamy mixture.
Add chocolate chip.
Spread into 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10-15 min., until brown.

title: sausage chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain sausage.
Add cheese, cut into chunks and cook until melted.
Add BLT Ranch salad dressing. Spray 2 cookie sheets with olive oil cooking spray.
Line won ton wraps on sheets.
Spray tops of won ton wraps with olive oil spray. Spoon sausage mixture by heaping teaspoonful onto middle of wraps. Fold each wrap across to opposite corner to form triangle.
Seal edges of wrap together by pressing firmly together.
Continue to add wraps until sausage mixture is gone.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until brown and crispy.

title: tortilla soup
directions: When chicken and vegetables are done, add instant rice and cook until rice is done.
Add tortilla strips

title: corned beef dish(quick fix)
directions: Pour enough cooking oil into skillet.
Heat for frying potatoes.
Fry potatoes until golden.
Drain on paper towels to remove and absorb all surplus oil.
Salt lightly.
Pour off all cooking oil from skillet, leaving enough to fry chopped onion until tender, but do not brown onion.
Add chopped corned beef. Stir and cook mixture about 5 or 6 minutes, then add fried potatoes.
Mix well; stir constantly.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: hopping john
directions: Wash beans and pick over, removing any pebbles or dirt.
Add cold water to cover.
Soak 12 hours or overnight.
The quick-soak method can be used.
If using fresh peas, this is not necessary. Rinse peas and drain.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken.
When it is done, wrap in Reynolds Wrap.
Put in the refrigerator to cool.
Dice chicken with a sharp knife.
Add 1/2 cup celery and pickles.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise so that it will hold together.
Delicious!

title: schweinerippchen in krautersosse
directions: Trim ribs; cut into 4 to 8 sections.
Arrange ribs in a shallow dish.
In a small bowl, combine wine, jam, salt and pepper.
Pour wine mix over ribs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally, and spooning marinade over ribs. Remove ribs from marinade and drain well, reserving marinade.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Cut up chicken and wash well.
Pat dry with paper towels. Salt and pepper chicken, then dredge in flour.
In hot skillet with Crisco, brown chicken.
(It doesn't have to be done, just browned some.)
Remove chicken to platter.
Saute onions, celery, pepper and rice.
Place the rice mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle on one package dry onion soup mix.
Now arrange browned chicken on top of rice.
Pour 2 cups of water over all.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Toast muffins.
Top each half with Canadian bacon, poached egg and warmed Hollandaise Sauce.

title: asparagus
directions: Cover with milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 30 minutes on moderate heat.
Bake, covered.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute hamburger meat and onion together.
Place in crock-pot. Add other ingredients and cook on high until hot.
Reduce heat to low and cook 8 hours.
Add water, if needed.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine pound cake mix, egg, butter and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into jelly roll pan. In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk.
Add eggs, pumpkin, pumpkin pie spice and salt and pour over unbaked crust.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until set.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: a bowl of red
