directions: In a large heavy pan, brown beef and cook onion with chili, cumin and garlic until tender. Add gravy, tomatoes, salt and red pepper. Cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Stir now and then. Add beans and corn meal. Cook, stirring for 5 minutes or until thickened. Makes about 14 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown bacon in skillet.
Add the following, raw: potatoes, carrots, peas, hamburger and onion.
Season to taste.
Cover and cook until done.
Stir several times.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix together beef, rice, onion, ketchup, egg, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Cut tops from peppers and remove membrane and seeds.
Wash clean.
Spoon ingredients into peppers.
Put 2 cups water into roaster, peppers and a can of Italian stewed tomatoes over peppers; bake.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain. Add 3 cups water and bouillon cubes. Mix sour cream, flour and garlic powder along with a little water so it can be easily mixed.
Pour sour cream mixture into pan with ground beef and water mixture. Cook and drain 10 ounces of noodles. Pour sour cream, ground beef mixture over noodles. Simmer until ready to serve.

title: roast duck
directions: Thoroughly wash the dressed duck.
Season with salt and pepper inside and out, using 1 teaspoon salt to the pound of duck and pepper to taste.
Peel, wash and slice onion.
Core, wash and slice apple.
Stuff duck with onion and apple slices; truss.
Place duck on rack in roaster.
Put 2 cups hot water in bottom of roast pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes to the pound, covered.
As duck bakes, baste with hot water to which butter is added.
The liquid from the duck is strong and should be poured off after duck bakes about 1 hour, then basting is started.
When done, remove onion and apple.
Replace with dressing.
Steam 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and cheese; spread half in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine zucchini and carrot; spread over crumbs.
Mix soup, sour cream and onion; pour over vegetables. Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Remove dark outer leaves from cabbage; wash and set aside. Core cabbage head.
Add 1 teaspoon of vinegar to approximately 3 quarts of boiling water.
Reduce heat to simmer; carefully place cabbage in water.
Remove leaves with tongs as they loosen.
Turn cabbage from top to bottom each time a couple of leaves are removed; drain well.
When cool, trim center veins from leaves, beginning at narrow part.
Save several small leaves for meat mixture.
Trim dark leaves and cover the bottom of a 5-quart crock-pot or a 6-quart Dutch oven.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; add to egg mixture.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour batter in and bake in 325° preheated oven for 1 hour or until tested done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.
Cool and frost.

title: crunchies
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave. Add Cap'n Crunch, Rice Krispies, pretzels and salted peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: coconut islands
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Melt the chocolate in the hot coffee in small saucepan over low heat. Cool.
Cream the Crisco and brown sugar. Add the egg and chocolate mixture. Cream together.
Measure the sour cream.
Add alternately with the dry ingredients. Stir in the coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Frost while warm.
Sprinkle tops with coconut.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: oyster stew
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add potatoes and onion.
Cook for 6 minutes on medium-high heat.
Add butter, mustard and pepper. Cook 4 minutes.
Add half and half milk and oysters.
Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Salt to taste.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix sugar, pudding and cinnamon together as a dry mixture. Let bread stand until thawed.
Make balls out of dough the size of a walnut; dip in melted butter and roll in dry mixture.
Place in angel food cake pan in layers.
Let stand 1/2 hour until raised. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.
Pull apart and enjoy.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Mix water,
molasses and baking soda; add to remaining crumbs (will be very thin batter).
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups reserved crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and soda together.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix with a fork.
Bake in an oblong pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar icing.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then liquid ingredients.
Knead until a large ball forms.
You may
need a little more flour, so as not to be hard to handle.
In another bowl (mixing bowl), grease the bowl, bottom and sides, before adding the dough.
Place dough into bowl and turn over so as to have oil on both sides.
Cover the bowl with Saran Wrap and place on cookie sheet so the rising dough will not spill oil from the sides of bowl into your oven.
Place in your oven; turn your oven light on for added heat to speed rising.
Let rise all night.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together vanilla pudding and banana pudding.
Blend together cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put half of Cool Whip in pudding mix.
Stir together and put remaining Cool Whip on top of pudding.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well and pour over meat balls to cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares(no-bake)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together & press into 9x12 pan.
Melt chocolate chips & spread over mixture.
Refrigerate until set. Cut into squares and serve.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: apple pumpkin streusel muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine, until mixture is crumbly.
To be sprinkled on top of muffins.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine dates, raisins, water and soda in mixing bowl; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar, beating well at medium speed on an electric mixer.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add date mixture, stirring until well blended.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool cans 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks; cool completely.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: creamy chicken and chile enchiladas
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick spray. Cook chicken until no longer pink. Add cream cheese and chiles. Cook over medium heat until blended well. Spoon filling into tortillas and roll up. Place tortillas seam side down in lightly greased casserole dish. Pour enchilada sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in 400° preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 30 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: mom's dorcas cake
directions: Boil raisins 15 minutes in 3 cups water, then add 1 cup cold water, shortening and sugar. Mix dry ingredients together and add to raisin mixture. Do not overmix. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: grilled tuna teriyaki
directions: In a large shallow dish combine first four ingredients.
Put tuna in marinade.
Turn over to coat. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine butter, cocoa, sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and turn off heat.
Stir in peanut butter and quick oats. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate; set aside.
Combine apple juice and cornstarch in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Mix apples with Equal, flour and cinnamon.
Put into pie crust and dot with butter.
Add apple juice mixture to apples.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer in crock-pot all day.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrub carrots and slice in thin rounds; boil in salted water for 10 minutes or until crisp; do not overcook.
Drain well; add onion and bell pepper.
Mix gently.
Put tomato soup, vinegar, oil and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add Tabasco.
Pour over the carrots in a container of your choice; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps indefinitely.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Add to 3 tablespoons bacon grease the pepper, onions and potatoes.
Cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and melt.
Add the bacon pieces.
Break eggs into skillet and cook, stirring sparingly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit cocktail fried pies
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook and mash fruit as it cooks. Add 1/2 cup sugar; mix well, then stir in 2 tablespoons of cornstarch, mixed with 1/2 cup of water.
Add vanilla and let cool.
Roll biscuits or dough into thin circles.
Place 2 tablespoons of cooked mixture onto one-half of circle.
Fold over and seal by pressing with tines of fork.
Fry in hot oil or solid shortening until golden brown on both sides.
A mixture of white and butter Crisco is good for this recipe.

title: baked french toast
directions: Heat oven to 350° and butter a 4-inch deep x 10 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Place cubed bread in dish.
Mix half and half, eggs and 1/2 cup of the maple syrup until smooth.
Pour mixture slowly over casserole to saturate even top cubes.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until mixture puffs up.
Melt butter and 1/2 cup maple syrup together.
Drizzle over top and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: meat and beans
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain. Add beans and mushrooms.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add a small amount of water, if necessary.

title: chicken fettucini alfredo
directions: Cube chicken breasts into little squares. In a pan, saute chicken cubes in 2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt. Cook until chicken is done. Open alfredo sauce and pour over cooked chicken. Heat until warm. Cook noodles. Serve alfredo sauce over noodles.

title: peppers with cream cheese filling
directions: Rinse and dry peppers.
With sharp knife, cut off stem end, leaving small round of pepper attached.
Discard stem and finely chop the remaining part.
Remove seeds carefully without breaking skins.
Blend cream cheese with whipping cream until smooth.
Add cheese, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Blend well.
Add chives and finely chopped parts of peppers.
Fill peppers with cream cheese mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Cut into thin slices to serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix with Hellmann's mayonnaise or homemade mayonnaise.
Add a dash of pickle juice.
Do not mix with salad dressing.

title: shortcut cutout cookies
directions: Mix pie crust mix, powdered sugar and baking soda.
Stir in egg, water and vanilla until dough holds together.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until edges are light brown in 350° oven.
Remove from sheet.
Cool.
Decorate as desired.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pimento cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple and combine with other ingredients.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed. Gradually add the cooking oil. Pour into dry ingredients and mix well. Add frozen strawberries. Add nuts, if wanted. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Check for doneness and bake a few minutes longer if needed.

title: italian cole slaw
directions: Mix onions with sugar and set aside.
Shred (don't grate) cabbage.
Mix in small saucepan the remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling point.
Toss the onion mixture with the cabbage.
Pour the dressing over it while it is hot.
Toss and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Better made the day before. Keeps well.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet and drain grease.
Add tomatoes, green peppers, onions and jars of Cheez Whiz and mix well.
Simmer until well heated.
Serve with nacho chips.
Can also make in a fondue pot or crock-pot.

title: grandmother's oatmeal-coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in vanilla, oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake for 30 minutes at 350° in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cover top of cake with miniature marshmallows while still hot.
Let cool.
Prepare topping and top cake.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except corn and beans.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave for 2 hours or until meat pulls away easily from bone.
Add corn and green beans during last half hour of cooking.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Combine beef, sausage, garlic, onion and fennel in 4-quart casserole dish.
Microwave 15 minutes on High. Drain. Add tomatoes.

title: chicken with sherry mushroom sauce
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Place in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Dilute one can mushroom soup with 1/2 can water and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Dilute second can of mushroom soup with 1/2 can sherry and pour over chicken.
Bake another 30 to 45 minutes, basting every 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Spoon sauce over rice.

title: ratatouille(provencale vegetable stew)
directions: Heat oil in flameproof casserole.
Add onions and cook gently, until just limp.
Stir occasionally so they don't brown.
Add remaining vegetables and season with salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 30 minutes, until vegetables are tender, but not mushy, and most of liquid has evaporated.
If Ratatouille is still soupy, cook uncovered over low heat for another 10 minutes.
Just before removing from heat, stir in herbs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: benne brittle
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch shallow pan.
Place sesame seed in heavy skillet and stir over moderate heat until slightly brown.
Pour into bowl and set aside.
In the same skillet, melt butter and stir in honey.
Cook over medium heat for about 3 minutes.
Add sesame seed and continue to cook, stirring constantly, but not vigorously, until mixture turns golden brown, about 2 to 4 minutes.
Spread mixture in prepared pan while still hot.
With buttered knife, cut into squares immediately.
Cool.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Crumb Mixture:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter together.
Press into spring-form pan, 10-inches or 11-inches.
Set aside.

title: honey mustard dressing(great for spinach salad)
directions: In a large pot, simmer minced onions in blended oil until soft. Then add sesame oil, honey, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar. Whisk together well and continue to simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 5 quarts.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together and pour over Crispix.
Stir well.
Put powdered sugar in brown bag and pour cereal into bag. Shake well!
Store in airtight container.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all well and pour into a large casserole.
Top with 3/4 box Cheez-It crackers and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great for covered dish meals.
It makes a large amount.

title: chili rice dish
directions: Prepare rice, then mix green chilies, sour cream and 1/2 pound grated Monterey Jack cheese throughout rice.
Dot with butter. Cover with another 1/2 pound grated Monterey Jack.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix the first four ingredients until blended.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pastry shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, sugar, Crisco, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Add pineapple, flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder; mix well.
Add nuts or coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Put a maraschino cherry on top of each. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: kay's strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch, jello and water to boil.
Turn burner on medium; boil for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Place cut strawberries in pie shells.
Pour filling over.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: carrot nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Put flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, salad oil and sugar.
Beat them all together, then add carrots, nuts, raisins (floured to keep them from sinking) and cinnamon.
Pour into buttered tube pan to bake 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Serves 10.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Microwave first 4 ingredients 4 minutes, stir and microwave 2 more minutes.
Add egg yolks and microwave 2 minutes.
(It should be thick at this point, but if not, cook a couple more minutes.) When thick, add vanilla and butter.
Let cool and pour into cooled pie shell.

title: garbage can dinner(for a very large crowd)
directions: In a new 30 gallon garbage can or large restaurant cooking container, place 2 inches of corn husks in bottom; add grate. Then add at least 2 inches of boiling water.
Place layers of vegetables and meat according to sequence.
Place on outdoor fire or grill and steam for 1 to 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Stir in package of dry jello.
Fold in fruit cocktail, cherries and pecans.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender and transparent.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and gradually add to the onions.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except raisins and nuts at low speed.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Add raisins and nuts at low speed; mix well.
Drop by spoonful about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven or until lightly brown around edges.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Good on anything you like to dip.

title: arroz con jocoque
directions: Layer in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish, topping with the grated Cheddar.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated, about 20 minutes. This is good with turkey or beef, as well as Mexican food.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix milk, egg and oil and add to dry ingredients.
Cook on hot griddle.
Serve with maple syrup or fruit sauce.

title: doris' jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, crushed pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour one half the mixture in a dish and let congeal.
Add sour cream to the other half of mixture; pour this over the first congealed layer.

title: pork and green chili casserole
directions: Stir-fry pork.
Stir in all other ingredients, except cheese. Pour into a 2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 6 patties.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place patties on rack and cook 5 minutes on each side or until done.
Brush top of each cooked patty with tomato sauce and top with a slice of cheese.
Yield:
6 servings (166 calories per serving).

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef in a skillet and drain; add taco seasoning and stir.
Add chili beans and simmer over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Spoon into the bottom of a casserole dish.
Top with cheese and then crumble corn chips on top until it forms a thin crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and top with fresh chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce.
Serve immediately, topped with taco sauce if desired.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Brown bacon; add onion and ground beef.
When cooked, drain off grease and add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes or simmer in skillet for about 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a bowl, mix apples and 1 cup sugar. Set aside. Mix oil and 1 cup sugar. Mix eggs, vanilla, flour, soda and salt. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until cake is done.

title: hixon's roast turkey
directions: Wash turkey; rub down with oil and melted margarine.
Add water to roasting pan with turkey.
Make a tent out of foil to cover the bird.
Place in oven at 325° and bake for 4 hours. Baste continuously.
Take pan drippings and add to dressing.

title: never fail doughnuts
directions: Mix thoroughly; roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut and fry in deep fat at 375°.

title: coconut bars
directions: Sift together white sugar and flour and set aside. Melt butter and mix in the flour and white sugar. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place this mixture in bottom of pan and spread it out. Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix powdered sugar, milk, vanilla and Cool Whip, then fold in cream cheese.
Make layers starting with cookies and ending with cookies.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, molasses and mix well.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture and blend.
Stir in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening; mix in zest.
Pour liquid all at one time.
Mix lightly enough to bind ingredients together.
Roll on lightly floured board to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine chopped apples and sugar and let stand in mixing bowl. Beat egg whites stiff; add yolks and beat.
Add oil and mix well. Let stand.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil and egg mixture to apples and sugar and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts and stir well.
Pour in well-greased and floured pan (Bundt pan).
Bake at 350° until cake is done.
Turn out of pan while cake is hot and drizzle with 1 cup powdered sugar dissolved in juice of one lemon.

title: mixed bean casserole
directions: Dice bacon and fry.
Remove bacon and drain on paper towels. In bacon fat saute garlic, onion, green pepper and celery.
Add and mix well the rest of the ingredients, except bacon.
Put bacon on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until beans are good and hot.
Bake in a 2-quart bean pot.
Serves 12.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt shortening in Pyrex baking dish.
Scald meal with boiling water.
Mix until mushy.
Add sweet milk and then eggs.
Mix well, then pour in shortening.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour
and
salt.	In saucepan, bring to a boil margarine,	cocoa
and water.
Pour over dry ingredients and add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour in greased 9 x
13-inch pan
and
bake 20 minutes at 400°.	Frost cake, if desired.

title: hamdogs (grilled)
directions: Mix 1st 5 ingredients.
Slit franks, cutting to ends and only 3/4 the way through.
Stuff with ham mixture.
Wrap with bacon. Secure with toothpicks.
Brush with barbecue sauce while grilling until bacon is crisp.
Serve in toasted buns.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie shell.
Put into pie shell. Freeze until solid.
May need to thaw some before serving.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together the oleo and shortening.
Gradually add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with each addition.
Sift together flour mixture and add with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into unbaked crust. Place in cold oven.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until the crust cracks.

title: cherry dream cake
directions: Slice angel food cake evenly in two, having top and lower section.
Spread pie filling onto bottom layer, on top only. Place the top section back over this.
Save a little of the pie filling.
Then, after the cake is restacked, cover it with Cool Whip like icing a cake.
Put remaining pie filling on top of the Cool Whip (on top of cake).
Keep in refrigerator.
Very good and keeps well.
Keep cake covered.

title: vegetarian burritos
directions: Microwave tortilla for one minute.
Lift and wipe excess moisture off plate.
Return tortilla to plate, adding to center broccoli (or spinach).
Top with cheese, then salsa.
Warm entire tortilla for one minute.
Remove from microwave.
Wrap by rolling (to eat with fork and knife) or fold one side up and then roll (to pick up).
Let cool one minute before eating.

title: nutty cracker crisp
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Cook for a few minutes. Cool.
Lay crackers on cookie sheets.
Dribble margarine and sugar on crackers. Top with crushed walnuts. Bake at 325° for approximately 10 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and lay on wax paper until cool.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with just the juice from one can of sweet potatoes.
Let them boil for about 5 minutes.
Pour off liquid and mash the potatoes well.
Then add the sugar.
Stir well.
Add crushed pineapple, including the juice.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Stir in onions, spinach, water chestnuts and red pepper. Cover; refrigerate to blend flavors. Serve with crisp vegetable dippers, assorted crackers or bread.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix together cinnamon, sugar and pecans and set aside.
Mix with mixer cake mix, sour cream, water, oil, eggs and pudding. Oil bundt pan and put 1/2 of cinnamon mixture.
Add 1/2 of cake mixture.
Add remaining cinnamon mixture.
Add remaining cake mixture.
Swirl with knife to create marble effect.
Bake 350 degrees for one hour.

title: spicy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 13 casserole dish. Melt cream cheese and butter. Whisk together milk, flour and salt. Add to cream cheese and butter mixture. Add drained corn and chopped jalapeos to mixture and pour into baking dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fluffy frozen peanut pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; pour into crust.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 or 4 minutes before cutting.
Keeps well frozen for 2 weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice in water.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese. Cover with cheese and bake in a covered dish at 325° until done.

title: pat's pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla; add butter and pecans.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch shallow pie shell.
Cook about 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: appetizer quesadillas
directions: Fry tortillas one at a time in hot oil in skillet until crisp and golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle mixtures of cheese over tortillas.
Top with tomato.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until each cheese melts. Cut each tortilla into quarters.
Top with cilantro.
Serve warm. Yields 3 to 6 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine juices and sugar.
Mix.
Add fruits and spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze (cover with foil).
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Beat margarine, egg, sugars, and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients:
flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Then add the oatmeal, Rice Krispies, and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: "the cake that won't last"
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Then add the rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Do not beat.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato gratin with boursin cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Stir whip cream and cheese in large heavy saucepan over medium heat till cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Arrange half of sliced potatoes in baking dish in slightly over-lapping rows.
Generously season potatoes in dish with salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 of cheese mixture over potatoes.
Arrange remaining potatoes as before. Salt and pepper generously.
Pour remaining cheese mixture over potatoes.
Bake till top is golden brown and potatoes are tender when pierced with a knife, about 1 hour.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into loaf.
If mixture seems a little dry or stiff, add a little milk (1 or 2 tablespoons).
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 35 minutes.
Good recipe for high cholesterol sufferers.

title: crabs
directions: Wash crabs. Place in pot. Boil until done. Eat with hot sauce.

title: pasta vegetable
directions: Cook pasta noodles as directed.
Saute onions and bell pepper in canola oil.
Add broccoli and corn.
Steam for 15 minutes, then add pasta.
Season with Nature's Seasons.
Also can add 1 pound sauteed summer smoked sausage.

title: squash-tomato casserole
directions: Mix squash, tomatoes and seasoning.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for approximately 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Replace cover; let stand for approximately 5 minutes before serving, until cheese melts.

title: bierocks
directions: Follow directions on hot roll mix package.
While dough is rising, brown hamburger, onion and cabbage in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer on low while dough rises.
After dough rises once, roll out to approximately 1/4-inch or thinner.
Cut into 4-inch squares and spoon on meat mixture.
Bring corners up and pinch closed.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° until golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour on.
Bake additional 20 minutes.

title: lemon glazed cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients thoroughly. Press crust evenly onto bottom and sides of buttered 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add sugar, blending thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in lemon juice, rind and vanilla. Blend well.
Turn into spring-form pan.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: black beans
directions: Rinse black beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Cook black beans in same water about 1 1/2 hours.
Saute onions, green peppers and garlic in olive oil.
Add to black beans.
Add oregano, salt and pepper and bay leaves.
Cook over low heat for approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until beans are tender and liquid has thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vinegar just before serving. Serve over yellow or white rice.

title: chocolate-peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly. Stir in corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Sprinkle chocolate chips over the bottom of an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour filling into pie shell. Cover the edges of pie with foil. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 15 to 20 minutes more or until knife comes out clean.
Chill.
Garnish with Cool Whip and chopped peanuts. Makes 8 servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Start to let jello set up. Mix the cottage cheese, chopped pecans and fruit cocktail. Add to the jello, then top with marshmallows.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Dust steaks well with flour.
Dip in egg and then in bread crumbs to coat evenly.

title: williamsburg orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Measure all ingredients, except frosting, into a large mixer bowl.
Blend
1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Frost cake with frosting.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for at least 3 days before serving.
Spoon desired amount over brick of cream cheese; serve with crackers.
This sauce is also excellent with baked ham.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: In a large baking dish, mix together the first 4 ingredients. Lay chicken and onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: krumkake
directions: Whip cream, then add egg, sugar, flour and then vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake on krumkake iron, heated to medium-high, about 15 seconds.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse with hot water.
Add milk and beaten eggs to spaghetti.
Put into a jelly roll pan.
Top with sauce, then hamburger pieces (no need to brown first) and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Chop up Butterfinger bars.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer and follow manufacturers directions to churn.

title: strata
directions: Remove sausage from casing; brown for 10 minutes.
Add green peppers and onions; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook 15 minutes more.
Slice bread.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with butter. Put bread in bottom of dish.
Pour meat mixture over bread; top with more bread.
Beat eggs, milk and salt; pour over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour or overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pressed butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; stir in vanilla.
Add salt and flour, stirring flour one cup at a time. Press dough through cookie press onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until cookies brown on edge.
Makes approximately 7 dozen.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13 pan. Poke holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon. Mix Jell-O with 1/2 cup hot water. Add 1/2 cup cold water. Pour over cake. Mix milk and pudding well. Blend pudding mix with Cool Whip. Add orange extract. Frost cake and chill overnight.

title: white fudge
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, syrup and butter for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: watermelon rind pickle
directions: Peel and
cut rind into 1-inch wide squares.
Soak rind in water
and
lime
mixture	overnight
or
hours
(use enamelware	or
crockery).	Cover
rind completely in mixture. After soaking,
rinse
well,
boil	20 minutes in clear water. Drain and cool in ice water until rind is cold.
Drain and dry each piece	of
rind
with	clean
cloth.
Mix sugar, vinegar, water and oil of cloves; pour over rind and cook until rind is clear;
approximately
hour.
Pack
jars with rind and fill with syrup.
Wipe
top
of	jars clean, seal with boiled lids. Cover jars after sealed with a towel to hold heat to the lids. Makes 8 quarts.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown and onions are tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer about two hours stirring often to prevent burning.

title: chocolate covered coconut
directions: Mix well.
Shape in small bricks.
Dip in chocolate chips and paraffin.
Drain on wax paper.

title: pork chops gutmann
directions: Mix corn flakes and Bisquick.
Dip chops in water, then in Bisquick, flake mix.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then pour soup over chops and return to oven for 20 to 30 more minutes.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Crumble
hamburger
in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Microwave at High
to 6 minutes, or until meat loses most of its pink color. Break
up	and drain.
Stir in potatoes, soup and salt.
Cover with
wax
paper.
Microwave
on
High
14 to 18 minutes,
or until potatoes are tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring	after half
the
cooking	time.
Stir
mixture
and sprinkle onion rings
(may
use entire can or less) over top. Microwave, uncovered,	at
High
1/2 to 3 minutes, or until heated.

title: berry orange cooler
directions: In blender, combine orange sherbet, thawed strawberries in syrup and orange juice.
Blend until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 can (12 ounce) or 1 1/2 cups of ginger ale.

title: savory italian vegetables
directions: In large skillet, electric or not, cook veggies until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
May need to add a little water.

title: slippery pot pie
directions: Add any seasonings to suit taste.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Cook raisins in water 10 minutes.
Cool and drain.
Cream together brown sugar, butter, oatmeal, soda and flour.
Pat 1/2 to 2/3 mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
While above is baking, mix in saucepan over medium heat the egg yolks, sour cream, sugar and cornstarch.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Add raisins, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice. Pour this mixture over baked crust.
Crumble remaining oatmeal mixture over the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour. Add to rhubarb and mix. Beat eggs lightly with fork and stir into rhubarb mixture. Make pie crust from favorite recipe. Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust; dot top with butter. Put either whole or lattice crust over top of pie. Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes. Let pie get cold before serving.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix and put into a spring-form pan with a graham cracker crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and 55 minutes at 300°.

title: iron skillet corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, baking soda and sugar together.
Add liquids to dry mix.
Pour in a preheated 9-inch iron skillet in which 1 tablespoon oleo is melted.
Bake 30 minutes in 450° oven.
Mixture is very thin before baking.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in walnut-sized balls.
Roll in sugar.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana-peanut parfait
directions: Stir bananas into pudding.
Combine chocolate and peanuts. In parfait glasses, alternate layers of pudding and choco-peanut mix.
Begin with pudding and end with chocolate mix.

title: double blueberry sundaes
directions: Combine 1 cup blueberries, maple syrup and lemon juice in saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 4 to 5 minutes or until blueberries have popped and sauce is slightly thickened.
Add remaining blueberries.
Heat through.
Serve warm or at room temperature, spooned over ice milk or ice cream.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown beef.
Add celery and onion when beef is almost brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix; put in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir into or serve over 1 can of chow mein noodles.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and green chilies in large Dutch oven (large pot).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 10.
Freezes well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pudding mix and reserved juice in bowl.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and pecans; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping gently.
Chill until serving time.
May add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour; beat well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Use a tube pan. This makes a large cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix together the milk, soup and onions.
Add the Creamettes, eggs, cheese and chicken mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Wrap ready made biscuit around vienne sausages.
If desired, cheese can be placed with sausages inside.
Heat oven to 375° to 400°.
Cook until biscuits are done.

title: strawberry margarita dessert
directions: Just before serving, blend all ingredients until smooth.

title: aunt gloria's heath bar cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(Makes 20 cookies.
Use an ice cream scoop to make and flatten down with your hand or use a tablespoon for smaller cookies.)

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla and blend well.
Add zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and add to batter.
Stir in pineapple, undrained. Add nuts and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Mix oleo, flour, oatmeal and brown sugar; press in a cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes, just until golden brown.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes, then crumble all up.
Spread half the mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream sugar and oleo, then add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Mix with rest of ingredients.

title: easy vegetable lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles as package directs.
Saute celery, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in small amount of water.
Mix vegetables and olives with sauce.
Put half drained noodles in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Add half vegetable-sauce mixture.
Add cottage cheese by spoonfuls to casserole.
Add remainder of noodles.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk, water, sugar and oleo, stirring until oleo is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Add rice and salt.
Cook until rice is tender (about 45 minutes).
Turn heat off.

title: calico beans
directions: Sauce onions, green peppers and beef together.
Add crumbled bacon.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate rum balls
directions: Break cookies into small pieces and crumble as much as possible.
Mix with other ingredients to form a stiff dough.
Use cookie crumbs to thicken and rum to thin as necessary.

title: roast beef gravy
directions: After cooking roast, remove roast to platter.
Pour fat from the roaster, reserve at least 4 tablespoons.
Add can of beef broth to pan.
Let stand a few minutes, scrape loose any browned particles.
Measure 4 tablespoons of fat into heavy skillet.
Add 4 tablespoons of flour and cook, stirring until brown.
Add 2 cups booth and cook stirring until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer pans lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool completely.
Remove from pans.
Makes 2 layers.

title: lyle's corn scallop
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the cheese.
Pour corn mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 30 minutes or until mixture feels firm to the touch.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all and force through cookie press (star design).
Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt the butter or margarine. Beat together the melted margarine, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla flavoring to margarine mixture. Mix together thoroughly.
Pour mixture into rectangular baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Makes 20 squares.

title: cucumber stew salad(serves 4)
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Dice onion.
Combine salad dressing, vinegar and 2 tablespoons water.
Set aside.
Add onion, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Sprinkle paprika gently on top for color. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Toss with cucumbers and onions in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally.

title: orange julius
directions: And a little heaven of prayer

title: boiled chocolate icing
directions: Wonderful on white cake!! Punch holes so it can go
into cake.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: o'henry(candy)
directions: Mix over low heat the brown sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter.
Add the corn flakes, Rice Krispies and peanuts and mix well.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet (1/2 to 1 inch deep) or in 2 pans, 9 x 9-inch.
Place in the fridge until set.

title: noble grand's chili
directions: Have the shredded Cheddar, chopped green onion and tortilla chips ready.
In a microwavable bowl, brown meat.
Add onions; brown.
Add all ingredients, except the last 3; simmer until bubbly and well combined.
Serve hot with remaining ingredients. Serves 4.

title: "miss jessie's party punch"
directions: Mix
frozen
juice concentrates with water according to can directions.
Add
other ingredients.
Will serve 25 to 30 people.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with milk. Mix all ingredients except the nuts. Pat into an 8-inch pie pan. Spread nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot with crackers or sturdy chips.

title: mother's dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and add water last.
Roll on floured board and cut.
Drop into boiling soup.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Do not cover while cooking.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Prepare any flavored packaged cake mix as package directs. Fill flat-bottomed wafer ice cream cones 2/3 full with cake mixture.
Stand cones on a jelly-roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake according to package instructions for cupcakes; cool.
Frost and decorate with colored sprinkles.

title: *thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: jam bars
directions: Sift
together	flour,	baking	powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir in oats
and
brown
sugar.
Cut
in
butter until crumbly. Pat about
of	this
mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread
with jam.
The jam will spread easier if you beat
it with
a
fork
before
spreading.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut while warm.

title: praline bars
directions: Spray sheet cake pan or cookie sheet (with sides) with Pam. Lay whole graham crackers flat in pan covering entire bottom.
If necessary, fill in any gaps with broken crackers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo and dissolve sugar in saucepan, then boil for 2 minutes.
Add pecans and pour evenly over crackers and bake for 10 minutes.
Before completely cool, cut into bars of desired size. Makes about 36 to 42.

title: tex-mex stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add beans, salsa and pepper to taste.
Simmer, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until thickened.
To serve, cut an X in top of each potato.
Fluff potato with fork.
Spoon beef mixture over each potato.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream and sprinkle with chopped green onion and tomato.
Serve with corn chips, if desired.

title: cocktail cheese cookies
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies.
Use your hands and mix well.
Takes a lot of elbow grease.
Roll small balls and press flat on cookie sheet; mash with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: my spaghini stick-to-your ribs soup
directions: Cook meat. Drain and set aside. Return to kettle and add water and next 10 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring once in awhile. Break pasta in half. Stir into soup and cook 5 minutes. Serves 13.

title: best ever cheese cake
directions: In bottom of snap pan, press mixture of margarine and vanilla wafers.
In large bowl, whip egg yolks.
Add sugar; whip until light.
Add flour; mix well.
Add cream cheese; mix very well. Mixture should be smooth.
Add sour cream; mix.
In separate bowl, whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cheese mixture; do not beat.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Turn oven off; do not open oven for 1/2 hour.
Open; leave cake in oven 1/2 hour more.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix beef, soup, oatmeal and pepper well.
Add eggs, salt and barbecue sauce.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken hot rice dish
directions: In a 9-inch square pan, layer rice, peas, chicken and soup. Top with 1 cup finely crushed Cheddar cheese crackers (Better Cheddar, Cheese Nips, etc.), mixed with 3 tablespoons softened butter.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp in enough water to cover with salt and seafood seasoning.
Boil until pink; drain, peel and devein.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Put shrimp in sauce and marinate overnight in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and spices in heavy pan; mix thoroughly.
Add water, vinegar and eggs; beat vigorously with rotary beater for a few minutes.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cool.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: apple salad
directions: Put Jell-O in a saucepan. Drain pineapple; add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Let come to a boil. Add cream cheese and marshmallows; let dissolve. Put in long Pyrex dish. Add pineapple and apples, then Cool Whip. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: cool taco salad
directions: In large bowl with tight sealing lid, layer ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving. The longer it sets the better it gets!

title: tea eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 20 minutes over low flame.
Cool in water.
When cool, drain eggs and tap the shells all over with the back of a spoon until the shell is completely cracked.
Return eggs to pan, cover with cold water, salt, soy, anise and tea.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer very slowly for 2 to 3 hours.
Turn off flame and leave eggs in liquid for 8 hours.
Tea eggs are then drained and left in their shells until ready to use.
Keep well wrapped in the refrigerator (up to 1 week).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Precook chicken.
Cut chicken into long pieces.
Prepare rice as directed.
Saute onion, celery, mushrooms in margarine. Combine rice, vegetables, chestnuts, mayonnaise and soup in a large casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: In large bowl mix pineapple juice with dry pudding.
Add pineapple chunks, fruit cocktail and oranges.
Mix well and chill.

title: miss betty's drop tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, butter and vegetable oil.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients very well.
Drop from teaspoon onto a cookie sheet. Press with a fork.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix the soup and sour cream together and reserve. Break up the flour tortillas into pieces, about 2-inches. Spray lasagna pan with cooking oil. In a lasagna pan, begin layering with tortilla pieces, soup, chicken and shredded cheese. Continue until pan is full, ending with the soup. Bake approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Mix batter and pour into 9 x 9 inch square pan.
Mix dry ingredients of topping together.
Sprinkle over top of batter. Gently pour water over top.
Bake at 400 degrees until done. Batter will rise to top during cooking.
Cake and pudding will be underneath.
Serves 4.

title: cauliflower italian style
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender. Chop into small pieces.
Beat eggs. Add crumbs, cheese, cauliflower, salt and pepper.
Make them like a pancake.
Fry until golden brown.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: On a large plate, spread refried beans.
Combine sour cream and seasoning; spread on top of beans.
Combine avocado, salsa and lemon juice; spread on top of sour cream layer.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over the top.

title: dilly crackers
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: garlic grilled lamb chops
directions: Trim excess fat from lamb chops.
Place chops in a shallow dish.
Combine soy sauce and remaining ingredients; stir well. Pour over lamb chops.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Remove chops from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill chops over medium coals, 8 to 10 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness, basting frequently with marinade.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan over medium heat until thick and clear; cool.
Add strawberries and pour into crust.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and top with 1/2 cup butter or margarine and 1/2 cup cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter.
Saute vegetables 5 minutes over low fire.
Blend in flour.
Then add chicken stock.
Bring to a boil.
Season and let simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add cream.
Perfect for a cold winter afternoon.

title: holy cow caramel cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to box directions. As soon as you take the cake from oven, punch holes in it with the handle of a wooden spoon. Pour whole can of Eagle Brand milk evenly over cake. Next, pour caramel over cake. Refrigerate overnight. Remove; spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle with crushed Heath bar.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 7 x 11-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: autumn surprise cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar, let stand until juice forms.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to apples.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Mix butter and sugar in a large bowl.
When creamy, beat in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, 1/4 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Mix in candied cherries and pecans.
Divide dough in half and shape each half into a cylinder (10-inches long and 2-inches in diameter).
Roll each in coconut, then wrap in wax paper and chill until firm (2 hours or longer).
Heat oven to 375°.
Slice dough into 1/4-inch thick rounds and place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef and onions. Drain. Cut cabbage into cubes. Add V-8 juice. Cook at low heat until cabbage is tender.

title: clear orange sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in orange juice and boiling water.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter and grated orange rind.
Serve warm. Makes 2 cups sauce.
Good on angel cake or white cake.

title: easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans. Combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Pour half the batter into each pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan.
Glaze and garnish as desired.

title: country baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Arrange in single layer in melted buttered casserole skin side down and bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn pieces and bake 20 minutes more until nicely browned.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine milk, soup, cheese, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Add onions and mushrooms to chicken.
Pour milk mixture over all. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and continue baking 30 minutes more at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and peanut butter morsels in a 2-quart batter bowl.
Melt for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Mix in peanuts and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Arrange bread cubes in bottom of greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with sausage and cheese. Whisk eggs and next 4 ingredients. Pour over casserole. Cover and chill overnight. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: pork's red chili stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in heavy frypan; add pork strips and garlic.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add green beans; stir-fry until beans and pork are done, about 5 minutes.
Push meat and beans to one side of pan.
Add sugar, soy sauce, chili peppers and ginger. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add oil and vinegar.
Stir pork and beans into the mixture to coat.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: snack-time mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Yields 7 cups.

title: instant pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Place mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over and add mushrooms and pepperoni.
Spread shredded Mozzarella cheese over.
Beat eggs, milk, oil and flour in bowl; mix well.
Pour over all and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 400° oven about 30 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until soft.
Do not brown.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook for 5 minutes. Gradually add the hot chicken stock, stirring until smooth. Simmer for 7 to 8 minutes until thick and smooth.
Add hot milk and cream.
Season to taste.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine ingredients. Chill overnight and serve with Fritos.

title: southwest chicken skillet
directions: *Ro-Tel brand "Diced in Sauce" Tomatoes and Green Chilies.

title: "stress" cookies
directions: Put all this in a huge bowl and mash, knead, squeeze and beat it until you have worked out all your frustrations.
The more you beat this mixture, the better it is.
Form into small balls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bacon crisps
directions: Put heaps of cheese on top of each cracker.
Wrap in bacon (does not require a toothpick).
Place on a broiler pan rack. Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
No need to turn over.
Leave on pan to drain.
Enjoy hot or cold.
May be frozen.

title: stone soup
directions: Read the story Stone Soup, where some weary travelers make soup with a stone and some offerings from some townspeople. Brown meat in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and cover with water.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours.
Don't forget to add a clean stone!!
Serves 25 hungry first graders.

title: cabin fever casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice potatoes, putting half into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Add ground beef, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, beans and onion.
Place remaining potatoes on top.
Combine soup and water; spoon over top.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: apple walnut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large mixing bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
In a small bowl, blend milk, molasses, butter and egg.
Stir in apple and nuts.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until combined (may be lumpy). Spoon into prepared cups.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; boil until done.
Alternate onion, potatoes, soup and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine all ingredients except baking soda; cook and stir until hard-crack stage or 290°.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda; stir until boiling stops.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Let set, then break into pieces.

title: hawaiian pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy, add eggs one at a time;
beating
well
after
each
addition.
Combine
flour, baking powder, salt and soda, add to creamed mixture.
Add milk while beating.
Add
remaining
ingredients.
Bake	in
a large tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix drained fruits with rest of the ingredients and chill overnight. quick and easy for a bachelor!

title: beef brisket
directions: Rub liquid smoke and seasoned salt on meat.
Wrap tightly in foil and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, add Worcestershire sauce and place in 250° oven in tightly wrapped foil for 5 hours. Allow no steam to escape.
Slice and serve with Barbecue Sauce.

title: pan coat
directions: Beat with mixer until smooth. Pour into plastic container. Close tightly and refrigerate. Use for coating cake pans and baking dishes. Eliminates flouring.

title: pat's tandy cakes
directions: Mix ingredients, except peanut butter and chocolate bar, until creamy.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour batter onto a greased and floured 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet or jelly roll pan and bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1 cup of the syrup.
Mash pears with fork or potato masher.
Heat syrup.
Pour over jello and stir until jello is dissolved.
Beat cheese with milk until smooth and blended.
Gradually beat in hot jello.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pears and cream.
Chill until set.

title: kathy's bread(3 grain; yields 6 loaves)
directions: In large saucepan, bring to boil 3 cups water and 3 tablespoons salt.
Mix together 1 cup cold water and 1 cup corn meal.
Add corn meal mixture to boiling water and cook until thick; remove and add 1 cup honey, 2 cups oats, 1 1/2 cups cold water and oil.
Mix together 1 cup warm water and 3 tablespoons yeast.
Let stand until bubbly.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients with onion, milk added to beaten eggs (must form soft ball).
Drop from teaspoon into deep hot fat.
Will float when done.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Pour in soups.
Add rice. Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook until thickened.
Add to potatoes and warm up.

title: moravian slaw
directions: Sprinkle 1/8 cup salt over cabbage, carrot, pepper and onion; let stand for about 2 hours, then squeeze out all water with your hands.
Discard water.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with pumpkin batter. Spread in well-greased and floured cookie sheet.
Spread nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Unroll and fill with filling.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil the fryer until done.
Remove the skin and take the meat from the bones.
Dice chicken, onion, celery and sweet pickles. Mix together in a large bowl and add mayonnaise.

title: pistachio salad or dessert
directions: Mix all together; cool and serve in large bowl or dessert dishes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook together first 6 ingredients until a firm ball.
Remove from fire; add vanilla and nuts if you like.
Beat.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool, then cut.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Roll chicken pieces, boned side up, on cutting board.
Working from center out, pound chicken with wooden mallet to make cutlets 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place ham slice and cheese on each cutlet.
Tuck in sides of each.
Roll up like jelly roll. Skewer or tie securely.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Chop hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Melt currant jelly and mustard to make sauce.
Place sauce mixture in crock-pot.
Add hot dogs and cook on low setting 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with toothpicks or cocktail forks.
Taste best when slow cooked several hours on low heat.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and slightly beaten eggs.
Add melted butter, vanilla, brandy, chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken fresno
directions: Pour lime juice over chicken in a large bowl; turn to coat. Let stand 1 hour, turning once or twice to season evenly.
Drain excess liquid from chicken.
Combine salt, pepper and paprika; sprinkle over both sides of chicken pieces.
Rub in with back of spoon.

title: brussels sprouts with bacon dressing
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts in water until tender or according to package directions.
Fry bacon until crisp, reserving bacon drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add vinegar and sugar to hot bacon drippings.
Cook mixture until sugar dissolves. Toss dressing over hot Brussels sprouts and serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in 325° oven.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: mexican enchilada
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain fat.
Stir in 1 package taco seasoning mix with 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for few minutes.

In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer seasoned meat, diced onion, corn tortilla shells (the flat round shells), then Velveeta cheese, then hamburger, onions, shells cheese, etc.; on the last layer, pour a 1/2 cup of seasoning over the shells to soften them so they don't dry out in the oven.
(Seasoning Mix = 1/2 package taco seasoning mix in a 1/2 glass water, stir up.)
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.
Serve with salad or top with tomato, lettuce and sour cream.

title: oil and vinegar salad dressing
directions: In a pint jar, add the vinegar, garlic salt and Sweet 'N Low. Fill the remainder of the jar with the vegetable oil.
Shake or stir to mix well.
Very good.

title: fig bar bread
directions: In a medium bowl, sift together flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine beaten eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Add to flour mixture, stirring until well blended.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix in crumbled fig bar cookies. Pour 1/3 of the batter into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle half of the fig mixture over the batter.
Pour another 1/3 of the batter into the pan and sprinkle remaining crumbs over.
Top with remaining batter.
With narrow spatula, swirl gently through batter and crumbs to marble.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to cool and remove from pan.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients and add milk, Egg Beaters, honey and oil.
Mix until just moistened.
Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Fill greased muffin tins or use muffin papers.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar, if desired.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: bologna
directions: Lay away three days to dry, then hang up and smoke.

title: mocha fudge topping
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stir together cocoa, sugar, brown sugar, coffee and cream.
Cook over medium heat until sugars dissolve. While stirring, heat to boiling and boil 1 minute.
Add butter; beat until blended.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit except bananas.
Add pudding.
Mix well.
Add bananas, sliced just before serving.
Chill.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix peanut butter, milk and extract until well blended. Gradually add sugar until smooth.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple and bananas.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Prepare jumbo shells according to directions on box.
Drain. In large skillet, melt margarine.
Add beef and pork.
Cook until lightly brown.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in sherry, cheese, salt and bread crumbs. Cool mixture for 10 minutes.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Pour 1 jar spaghetti sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange shells in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over the shells.
Top with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom and sides of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, cream butter, maple syrup and sugar at low speed until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Stir in orange juice and pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing just enough to blend.
Pour batter into pan. Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.

title: mexican tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Shape dough into small balls using approximately 1 teaspoon dough for each cookie.
Roll balls in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Flatten slightly.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on rack. Makes 4 dozen.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and all dry ingredients, sifted together. Beat well.
Add corn and Crisco.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil; brown on both sides.
Drain well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use double boiler. Mix sugar, flour, and salt. Add milk and water. Turn to medium-medium high heat. When mixture starts to thicken, add eggs. When thickened, remove from heat. Add vanilla. Layer wafers, bananas, and mixture. Repeat. Top with meringue. Brown top.

title: halloween spider doughnuts
directions: Cut three
pipe cleaners in half.
Bend into a V shape. Place three
of
these on opposite sides of a doughnut.
These are the legs
of the spider.
Make two small horizontal slits in the top at the front of the doughnut.
Place two M&M's (use the same color)
in
the
small
slits
as
if
the M&M's were standing on end.
These are the eyes.
Make another horizontal slit between and
below
the
"eyes." Place a M&M here for the "mouth." Use a different color for mouth.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, sugar, vanilla, eggs and 1/4 cup margarine and beat until smooth.
Put in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
To make topping, cut sugar and flour into 1/3 cup margarine until crumbly.
Add nuts and sprinkle on potatoes covering them completely.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add mashed bananas and eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add. Do not overmix.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cider punch
directions: Chill all liquids in refrigerator for several hours.
Before serving, combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Set punch bowl in a container filled with ice to keep it well-chilled (or place a block of ice in punch bowl).

title: reception salad
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple and add enough water to make one cup.
Heat liquid and dissolve jello.
Let jello mixture cool. Blend cream cheese, milk and pimentos.
Add to jello.
Add other ingredients and chill until firm.

title: sugared walnuts or pecans
directions: Mix sugar, salt, 1/4 cup water and honey in skillet or pan; heat at 250° until a little of mixture dropped in water forms soft ball.
Turn off heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts; continue stirring until thick and creamy.
Turn out on waxed paper and separate nuts with 2 forks to cool and harden.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Add water and salt to egg whites and beat with eggbeater until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
Add baking powder and beat until smooth and fluffy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add shredded zucchini and vanilla, then add flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and pecans. Bake at 325° for one hour.
Yields two loaves.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel and core pears.
Grind pears and lemon and orange (including the rind); use coarse blade of chopper.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Stir well.
Heat to boiling point.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot sterilized jars. Makes 9 (6 ounce) jars.

title: chocolate halfway cookies
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugar and brown sugar.
Separate eggs; add yolks, water and vanilla and blend.
Sift dry ingredients and add. Put in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining brown sugar.
Cover cookie mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage loaf
directions: Mix well all of the ingredients and place in a loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350°
for 1 hour.
Pour off any excess fat.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: asparagus and chive spread
directions: Finely dice asparagus in bowl.
Combine with mayonnaise, chives and salt and pepper.
Spread on bread and cut into 4 pieces.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: In 9-inch cast-iron skillet, cook bacon, over medium-low heat, until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain on paper towel.
Crumble and reserve.
In cup, reserve 2 tablespoons of bacon fat.
Discard remaining fat.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Cut pickles into thin strips.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Add spice and simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over pickles.
Refrigerate.

title: nut roll
directions: Melt butter.
When cool, add condensed milk, sour cream, regular milk, egg yolks, then crumble in yeast.
Keep stirring until yeast dissolves.
Sift flour, salt and sugar and add to liquid mixture and mix well.
Put in refrigerator overnight or for 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough into 8 pieces.
Roll each piece very thin in confectioners sugar.
Spread with nut mixture and roll like jelly roll.
Put three on cookie sheet (greased) and let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: basil-cheese potatoes
directions: Put it in the pan. Put the stuff in the pan. Then put in the oven shut it up.
For 100 hours then you take them out then you eat it.

title: peach pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan approximately 30 minutes.
Any kind of fruit is good for this (fruit cocktail, applesauce, etc.).

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut orange slices into small pieces.
With hands, mix all ingredients except nuts until well blended.
Shape into 1 large ball or 2 medium size balls, then roll in nuts to coat outside of cheese ball.
Chopped pecans or peanuts work well to roll cheese ball.
May also shape into other shapes and decorate as desired. Chill prior to serving.

title: all-purpose seasoning
directions: Use red pepper to personal taste.
Use less for mild and more for hot.
Use mixture like salt.

title: baked asparagus with parmigiano-reggiano
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Snap off tough bottoms of asparagus and discard.
Wash spears, pat dry, place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour olive oil over asparagus, roll until evenly coated.
Arrange spears in single layer and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage meat, stirring constantly to keep separated. When lightly browned, drain off fat and add cooked rice.
Place rice and sausage in a greased casserole.
Add soup; cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/4-inch pieces and press together to make a crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or golden brown. Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix cheese and chips together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly.

title: cold chicken and pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large serving bowl.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put sausage and cheese into bowl and place in microwave to soften cheese.
Then add Bisquick and mix with hands.
Roll out even balls and place onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together and serve with Granny Smith apple slices.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Best if used after 24 hours.
Use as condiment.

title: 24 hour slaw(fancy farm picnic slaw)
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil; pour immediately over the cabbage mix.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, Karo and peanuts in a 2 1/2-quart heavy pan. Cook on high heat, stirring constantly until hard crack (300°) or until syrup turns light amber.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda, beating rapidly until well mixed (about 10 seconds).
Pour onto a lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Do not spread or break.
Let cool. Break into pieces, then call me.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake in pan 15 minutes; then prick with utility fork.

title: dream cookies
directions: *Blended Oatmeal:
Measure and blend to fine powder.

title: nonfat seasoned french fries
directions: Spray a baking sheet with butter flavored cooking spray. Slice potatoes lengthwise to desired thickness.
Spray potatoes with cooking spray and season to taste with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown and crispy.
The crispness will depend on how much spray you use.

title: economy soup
directions: Cook potatoes until nearly done; add tomatoes, onion, salt and crisply fried bacon and season with bacon grease.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Mix jello and boiling water and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, sweetener and topping.
Blend jello and cream cheese mixture together and pour into the graham cracker crust.
Cool in the refrigerator and serve with fresh fruit slices or plain.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix green chilies and chopped olives into cream cheese. Spread onto tortilla shells.
Roll up shells and refrigerate approximately 3 hours.
Cut into 1/2 to 1-inch slices and serve.

title: cabbage dressing
directions: Beat 10 minutes with mixer.
Put in jar.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Add remainder of ingredients to the cocoa mixture.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased dish or pan.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and spoon off fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients except Mozzarella.
Layer 1/2 the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread 1/2 cottage cheese filling and 1/2 the Mozzarella and 1/2 the meat sauce.
Repeat layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (or fix early and refrigerate).
Bake 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: cake mix cookies
