directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring well (dough will be very sticky and hard to stir).
Stir in chopped pecans, if desired. Dust hands with powdered sugar and shape dough into 3/4-inch balls. Coat balls with powdered sugar and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: green beans
directions: Boil together on high heat for several minutes. Reduce heat and cook until most liquid is gone. Add salt only after tasting, since most home-canned beans have already been salted. Serve hot, as the last thing taken out of the pots before you sit down to eat.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar;
add eggs, milk, flavoring, salt and
coconut.
Mix
well
and pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° about 35 or 45 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread in bottom of round pan.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Shred Monterey Jack cheese over chili. Cover with foil; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: california chicken and fruit salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, celery and 1/2 cup almonds. Mix the mayonnaise with curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Combine with chicken mixture.

title: cheesy broccoli
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and let thaw in pan. Add soup, cheese, water chestnuts, and Accent.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Yield:
6 - 8 servings.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Peel and cut cucumbers in thin slices.
In a bowl add cucumbers, sour cream and salt; mix.
Amounts depend on your taste and the amount of people you will be serving.

title: baked bananas
directions: In small saucepan, combine juice, wine, honey, orange rind, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Heat until warm.
Peel bananas and slice in half lengthwise.
Place bananas, cut down, in greased baking dish large enough to accommodate without crowding them.
Pour sauce over bananas.
Sprinkle with almonds, a dot of margarine and coconut flakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: golden cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix flour, cheese, paprika and salt in bag or bowl.
Drop potatoes in cold water while you are preparing flour mixture, then put potatoes in flour mixture, coating well.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°, turning once.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs.
Add sliced bananas and mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, flour and salt.
Mix until all the flour is mixed in.
Fold in nuts.

title: broccoli and sausage casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fragrance of christmas
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and simmer on stove.

title: deviled egg surprise
directions: Devil the eggs and place halves in buttered casserole.
Add the shrimp and mushrooms.
Heat the white sauce and cheese together and mix well until cheese melts.
Pour over casserole contents and heat at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour hot water over the margarine; add brown sugar,
egg (beaten) and molasses.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and ginger.
Add to first mixture; mix well, using mixer.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: lemon-thyme baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter large baking dish.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Mix olive oil and melted butter together.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes or so. Combine lemon juice, thyme, salt and pepper.
Pour over baked potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake an additional 15 minutes. Remove from oven and serve on platter.
Serves about 6.
Tastes great as cold leftovers!

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring continuously.
Cook 4 1/2 minutes.
Pour half of mixture over chocolate and marshmallow cream.
Mix thoroughly and quickly.
Add rest of mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in lightly buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together. Stir in soup.
Mix in mixed vegetables and pour into an ungreased casserole dish. Cover with frozen Tater Tots and bake at 350° until Tater Tots are done.

title: ham and noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add ham, milk and beaten eggs.
Put in casserole and dot with butter.
Bake for 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet and decorate tops with rest of candy.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Some cracking should occur.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix well; form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes with a wax paper cover.
After baking for 30 minutes, remove the wax paper and continue to cook for 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir until thick and fudgy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cook ham hocks in Dutch oven over low to medium heat until hot. Reduce heat to low for 2 hours. Add onion, carrots and potatoes and enough water to fill pot about 3/4 full. Cook 1 hour. Add peas and cook 1/2 hour or until dry peas are done. Serve with cornbread.

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare pie crust as directed on package. In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and one of the eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Set aside.
Reserve hot fudge packet from brownie mix.
In large bowl, combine brownie mix, oil, one tablespoon water and remaining two eggs.
Beat 50 strokes with spoon.
Spread 1/2 cup brownie mixture in bottom of pie crust. Spoon and carefully spread cream cheese mixture over brownie layer. Top with remaining brownie mixture.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until center is puffed and crust is golden brown.
Pie may have cracks on surface. Place hot fudge packet in small bowl.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Stir in remaining tablespoon water.
Drizzle fudge over top of pie.
Cool 3 hours or until completely cooled.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour, white sugar and butter or margarine for base and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Add pineapple, cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Mix milk in last.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Combine.
To Use:
Add 4 tablespoons of mix into a cup of boiling water.

title: icey
directions: Mix 1 can each in blender. Finish filling with ice and grate. Repeat with remainder of juice, vodka and water.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve ingredients in warm water; add enough shortening as you would in making biscuits.
Make into dough as you would biscuits.
Let rise twice the size and knead down.
Make out and let rise again; cook.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup of water, mixing well to make a paste.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups water, egg yolks and butter, stir well.
Cook over medium heat about three minutes until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed of mixer; add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons of sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over hot filling.
Spread to edges of pie shell to seal the pie.
Bake at 450° for five minutes.

title: fudge candies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 8 to 10 minutes (start timing after it begins to boil).
Pour over remaining ingredients that have been put into larger bowl.
Mix well and pour into greased pan.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix melted butter, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan; bake 15 minutes.
Cool crust completely.

title: sugar free fudge
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate.
Stir in Equal and vanilla.
Combine with cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in lightly greased 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Refrigerate candy.
Does not keep well unless it is refrigerated.

title: that casserole
directions: Saute ground beef.
Add garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain. mix together cream cheese, sour cream, bell pepper and green onions.
Layer ingredients in casserole, beginning with noodles, meat sauce and sour cream mixture, ending with grated cheese on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yield:
4 servings, unless they're teenagers.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix Coca-Cola, mustard and catsup in saucepan and heat.
Salt and pepper the chicken.
Put the chicken in the sauce mixture. Reheat to full boil, turn heat down and let simmer about 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Follow directions on spaghetti seasoning package to make spaghetti sauce with meat.
Boil noodles according to package. Layer in a 2-quart baking dish:
2 noodles, sauce mixture, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese.
Layer again as above; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party meat balls
directions: Shape ground beef into small balls and brown slowly.
Spray pan with cooking spray.
Heat jelly and chili sauce.
Place browned meat balls into sauce mix; simmer for 2 hours.
Serve warm.
May use fondue pot and toothpicks for serving.

title: potato soup
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in canola oil.
Gradually add flour, stirring constantly to avoid lumps; cook until golden brown.
Add chicken stock; stir with a whisk.
Turn heat to low; add potatoes, bacon bits, skim milk and spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and onion, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Add hot sauce to taste.

title: easy orange marmalade
directions: Clean oranges with brush.
Grind one whole seeded orange. Peel 3 oranges and grind pulp.
Combine with sugar and boil over medium heat for 30 minutes stirring frequently.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Use heavy bottom pan for this.

title: hamburger mushroom casserole
directions: Shape meat into patties and fry, then add the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated green bean and peas salad
directions: Pour over pea and bean mixture.
Chill 24 hours.
Drain well. Serves 8 to 10.
A hit with all!
(Double recipe for a large crowd).

title: banana bread
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs in a large bowl with electric mixer for 3 minutes or until light and fluffy; stir in bananas. Sift flour, soda and salt onto wax paper.
Add gradually to butter mixture and stir until well mixed.
Add sour cream or sour milk; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with chopped walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center springs back when touched.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pan.

title: baked kielbasa
directions: Cook cut up kielbasa in water to remove excess grease.
Drain and add ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish lace cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in milk, flour and vanilla.
Stir in rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoonful (6 at a time 2 inches apart) on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
When you take them out, let stand for a minute until firm enough to turn with a spatula.
Turn upside down on the cookie sheet and roll in a cylinder.
Cool on rack.
Return to oven for a few seconds to soften if necessary.

title: venison roast
directions: Pierce roast and insert garlic halves into meat.
Place roast, bay leaf and vegetables into a large roasting pan.
Combine Lipton soup mix, cream of mushroom soup and water.
After arranging vegetables around and over the roast, pour the soup mixture over the top.
Cook approximately 3 hours at 350° or until tender.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Top with following.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Microwave cheese and salsa in a 1 1/2-quart bowl on High 5 minutes, stirring well after 3 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: granny george's old-fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar thoroughly; add egg and beat until creamy.
Add soda, dissolved in vinegar in a cup, then mix with the other mixed ingredients.
Add vanilla and then add flour gradually to make a stiff batter that can be rolled very thin. Cut out and bake at 350° until brown.
Sprinkle sugar on top while hot.
They are very crisp and continue to taste fresh after 2 weeks.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze to remove excess water. Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Serve with chips.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Into a blender container put roasted peanuts and 2 tablespoons peanut oil.
Blend until smooth, adding about 2 tablespoons more peanut oil gradually.
Add salt.

title: coconut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 6 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan for about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: deviled crabs or crab cakes
directions: Beat egg; add milk, pepper, salt and celery seed.
Melt butter and pour in.
Add crab meat and cracker crumbs.
Mold into shape and fry in deep fat.
Drain on wax paper.

title: glorified "round steak"
directions: Cook the wieners and partially fry the bacon.
Slit the wieners down the middle, placing a slice of cheese in the slit. Wrap bacon around the cheese and wiener.
Secure with a toothpick. Place on the griddle and cook until the cheese melts and the bacon is done.
You may prepare wieners the same way without a bun or eat with a fork.

title: great chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in remaining beef fat and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Serves approximately 8.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Bring margarine and chocolate to boil.
Add other ingredients. Mix well and put on top of marshmallow cream.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine pudding, Dream Whip and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Lay whole crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over the top.
Add another layer of crackers.
Pour rest of pudding over the top.
Cover with crackers.
Spread frosting on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and yeast.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise one hour.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cheese, dry dressing and mayonnaise together, preferably the night before. Spread cheese mix on bread generously. Place slice of cucumber on top and sprinkle with dill weed.

title: tortellini with spinach and clam sauce
directions: Wash spinach, remove stems, dry and place in a large bowl. Boil water; add salt and tortellini.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes, until al dente.
At the same time, heat clam sauce with olive oil, oregano and garlic powder until it starts to boil.

title: no sugar fruit dessert
directions: Drain cans of fruit (peaches, pears, fruit cocktail, etc.); reserve liquid.
You may have to add some orange juice concentrate or pineapple juice to have 4 cups fruit juice.
Use this to cook the boxes of pudding instead of milk.
Pour over fruit and toss. Chill and serve.
Makes for a crowd.
Half recipe for smaller portion.
Use what fruits are in season or your favorite.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat and cook without stirring until drop of syrup put into cold water forms a hard ball.

title: almond brittle
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam. Grease spatula.

title: cheese spread - veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Can be molded.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
(Drain all fruit before mixing.)

title: cloud nine brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Melt butter with 2/3 cup vanilla milk chips in top of double boiler over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In a large bowl of electric mixer, beat eggs, sugar and salt at high speed until very pale and thick, about 5 minutes.
Blend in melted mixture and vanilla at low speed.
Mix in flour just until combined.
Stir in remaining vanilla milk chips and semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Spread into prepared pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Top with be crusty and browned.
Cover with foil if browning too quickly.
Cool before cutting.

title: banana split cake
directions: Step 1:
Melt 1 stick butter.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onion in salted water until tender; drain. Mix ingredients and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Spoon onto platter.
Brown ground meat and drain.
Mix in water and taco seasoning mix.
Spoon meat over cream cheese.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, olives, chopped tomatoes and lettuce or anything else you think would taste good.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
While macaroni is cooking, place butter in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High for 1 minute or until butter melts.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Blend in milk.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring twice.
Add cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add the cooked and drained macaroni.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: excellent french toast
directions: Cube bread and cream cheese.
In a glass 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1/2 of the bread, all the cream cheese, then the rest of the bread.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and syrup; blend well.
Pour over bread and cream cheese layers.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn off oven; allow to sit in oven an additional 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and 1 cup mashed strawberries. Cook and stir until thickened. Line pie crust with sliced strawberries (3 cups). Pour cooked mixture over the strawberries. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: peppers in sauce
directions: Wash and remove seeds from peppers.
Slice onions.
Cover bottom of sauce pot or large skillet with oil.
Add onions and tomato sauce to peppers in pot.
Add salt to taste.
Cook until tender.
As peppers are cooking, wash 6 jars and fill with boiling water.
Boil lids and rings.
When peppers are tender, pour water from jars and fill with peppers and sauce.
Place lid on jar. Make sure rim is free from any sauce, oil or seeds.
Place ring on jar; tighten when lid is sealed.

title: vegetable (served hot) golden coin salad (served cold)
directions: Bring tomato sauce, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper to a boil; pour over carrots.
Add pepper, onion and celery.
Cook for a while.
Serve hot as a vegetable dish.
Refrigerate and serve cold as a salad.

title: creamed tuna royale
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cook green pepper, onion and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Add tuna and pimiento.
Heat to simmering; cook about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Serve over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: paradise icebox cake
directions: Do Ahead: Crush vanilla wafers and divide into 2 cups and 1 cup portions. Drain crushed pineapple and allow to continue to drain until any additional liquid is removed. Soften butter to room temperature. Thaw Cool Whip.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mash Blue cheese.
Add sour cream, lemon, sugar and water; stir.
Allow to chill 1 hour before serving.
Yields 10 servings.

title: pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are soft.
Take bone out and cut off ham.
Put rest of soup through blender or sieve.
Put pieces of ham back in and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs to mixture.
Mix sour cream and baking soda together and allow to foam.
Combine flour and salt.
Alternately add sour cream mixture and flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Mash bananas smooth and add to mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in a loaf pan.
Allow to cool in the pan 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: make-it-easy ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line baking pan with foil.
Place ham in pan , fat side up; coat with mustard and stud with cloves.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Layer pie filling in bottom glass baking dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Put in bag and put biscuits in and shake to coat well.
Place coated biscuits in greased Bundt or angel food pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: In blender, put peppers and juice or water and chop well.
In saucepan, melt margarine; add cheese and peppers.
Stir until cheese is completely melted.
Pour into containers and cool. Refrigerate.
May be heated to serve.
Serve with nachos.
You may add more or less peppers to taste.

title: shrimp cocktail cheese balls
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp.
Shape cream cheese into ball.
Place in small bowl with low sides.
Pour shrimp over cream cheese, then pour cocktail sauce over top. Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; put 1/2 in bottom of pan.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Spread berries in halves and spread over butter, egg and sugar mixture.
Whip cream and spread over berries.
Top with remaining vanilla wafers.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together and dip favorite fruit in it.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Bring to boil the remaining ingredients and pour immediately over cabbage mix.
Stir well and refrigerate.
Chopped green onions may be added.

title: no heartaches artichoke dip
directions: In an ovenproof bowl, combine the mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Drain the artichokes and add to the mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker pie crust; chill before serving.

title: ham and egg salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, tossing gently.
Combine next 4 ingredients and fold into ham mixture.
Chill well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Good way to use leftover Christmas ham.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well. Fold in Cool Whip, then add all the fruit and mix well.
Place in a bowl with lid that seals and place in freezer.
Remove about 15 minutes before ready to serve.
Serve soft.

title: caramel pecan pie via janis boyett
directions: Melt the caramels with the water and butter.
In a bowl, mix the sugar, eggs, vanilla, pecans and salt.
Pour the caramel mixture into the bowl and mix.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until set in middle.

title: spinach surprise
directions: Cook the spinach according to directions on package with the onion; drain well.
Add melted margarine and stir.
Add sour cream and stir.
Add vinegar and salt; stir.
Serve hot.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream first four ingredients and pat into 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
As soon as removed from oven, pour mixture of the other 3 ingredients on top.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Set in refrigerator.
Cut into desired size after well set.
Can be frozen.

title: salad greens a'la polonaise
directions: Mash the egg yolks and combine with mustard, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Vary proportion of lemon juice according to personal preference.
At the end, add sour cream.
Mix very well. Coat salad greens with the mixture and serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve.

title: cranberry party punch
directions: Combine juices.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Garnish with orange slices.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: fruit and wine appetizer(dutch recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour ginger ale over fruit.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove bones.
Add spaghetti to broth.
Cook. Let stand until broth is absorbed.
Combine chicken with soup and spaghetti.
Top with bread crumbs, grated cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Chop eggs.
Stir cheese until soft.
Add ingredients and shape into two balls.
Roll in parsley and garnish with egg slices.

title: sherbet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Add lemon rind.
Drop in Spry.
Add vanilla, milk and 1 egg.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining 2 eggs and yolk.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake in tube pan at 375° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and peanut butter until sugar is dissolved. Add to cornflakes.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry souffle salads
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup. Add enough water to syrup to make 3/4 cup liquid. Dissolve strawberry flavored gelatin and salt in boiling water. Add reserved syrup and lemon juice. Beat in mayonnaise or salad dressing. Chill until partially set. Whip with electric mixer until fluffy.
Fold in strawberries and nuts. Pour into 4 to 6 individual molds. Chill until firm.
Unmold atop slices of pineapple and place on lettuce. Serve with additional mayonnaise or salad dressing, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir pudding mix and milk in a saucepan; add egg yolks.
Stir constantly on low heat until a full boil. Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of cookies and sliced bananas in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; top with 1/3 of pudding.
Repeat layering and end with pudding layer.

title: jerries congo squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening; pour over brown sugar and stir until blended.
When cool, add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each one.
Add dry mixture, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour in greased 10 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: california casserole
directions: Cook mushrooms and onions in oleo.
Add flour, salt, pepper, Accent and milk to make a thick white sauce.
Add Cheez Whiz, Tabasco, soy sauce, artichoke hearts, beans and water chestnuts.

title: garlic-fried steak
directions: Put steaks in a large, shallow dish.
Pour a mixture of sour cream, garlic, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, celery salt and paprika over steaks.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Heat shortening in a large, heavy skillet.
Coat steaks with biscuit mix.
Brown on both sides in skillet.
Cook to desired doneness.

title: apricot-apple jam
directions: Grind apples and apricots. Add sugar and cook until thick. Makes 12 pints.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch pie shell; cool.
Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in a few drops of food coloring; cool.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Spray pan with Mazola cooking oil.
In skillet, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove.
Set aside.

title: famous pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove pie crust from freezer.
Combine ingredients in order given.
Re-crimp edge of deep dish crust only to stand 1/2-inch above rim.
Put on baking sheet.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake near center of oven for 70 minutes (45 minutes for regular crust).
Cool for 2 hours.

title: orange carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender; drain. In large saucepan, mix orange juice concentrate, butter, brown sugar, ginger, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until smooth and blended. Add carrots and parsley. Toss gently to coat.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add pecans, apples and vanilla.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Use as much as you want to taste and mix well.

title: potato salad
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes; heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook until tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain potatoes; cool.
Cut potatoes into cubes.
Stir in onion, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, toss with mayonnaise until potatoes are well coated. Stir in celery and eggs.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: nutty cocoa brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda and cocoa.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine butter and water in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until butter melts.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until blended

title: congo bars
directions: Melt shortening, stir in sugar and allow to cool.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add with nuts, and chocolate chips to shortening and sugar mixture.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Mix marinade. Add sliced tomatoes. Be sure all tomatoes are coated with marinade. Chill several hours, turning tomatoes at a time or two. Sliced green peppers and/or cucumbers may be added.

title: cherry walnut divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, salt and water to firm ball stage (248°). Pour slowly, beating constantly, over stiffly beaten egg whites. Beat until candy begins to stiffen.
Add candied cherries, flavoring and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or pour into well buttered pans.
When cold, cut in squares.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken as for frying.
Combine egg, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir until well blended.
Place the cut up chicken in this mixture and stir until all pieces are well coated. Set aside.
Crush enough Post Toasties or Rice Chex to make 2 cups of crumbs.

title: chocolate fudge(never grainy)
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar, salt and milk. Cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallows and vanilla.

title: beef chop suey
directions: Fry beef in oil over high heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove meat and keep hot.
To oil remaining in saucepan, add celery, onions, molasses (or dark corn syrup) and bouillon.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add bean sprouts.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Replace beef.

title: green beans moutande
directions: Mix the mustard, flour and salt in a double boiler.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Slowly add hot milk until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over beans.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until thread spins (250° temperature).
Add peanuts and stir constantly until temperature reaches 280°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and soda.
Pour onto buttered board to cool.

title: mammy's texas hash
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients and heat through.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake one hour at 350°.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix well in blender.
Serve with crackers.

title: eggplant resno
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until onion is golden. Add eggplant cubes, tomatoes, salt and sugar; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until eggplant is just tender.
Can sprinkle with cheese.

title: curried cottage cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: bundles of beans
directions: Drain beans.
Divide into 8 "bundles," wrapping each with bacon slice and securing with toothpick.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add brown sugar and garlic powder.
Bring to boil and remove from heat immediately. Pour over bean bundles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8. Great for company.

title: mexican egg cream
directions: In blender, combine half and half, egg substitute, chocolate syrup, instant coffee, vanilla and almond extracts. Blend smooth. Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain, mash and add other vegetables, soup and sour cream.
Mix stuffing and melted margarine.
Line bottom of casserole with this mixture, saving some to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jeanne's serbian quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onions with butter.
Dice ham into cubes and warm slightly.
Beat eggs; pour in cottage cheese, grated Monterey Jack cheese, onions and seasonings.
Pour half into pie crust.
Sprinkle with ham, artichoke hearts and mushrooms.
Pour the remainder of cheese mixture in.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife is clean. Let stand at least 5 minutes before cutting.

title: goofy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl except vinegar.
When mixture is mixed well, add vinegar and beat until foaming stops.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake in ungreased pan.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Lay frozen rolls in one layer.
Melt margarine in microwave.
Add sugar, pudding and cinnamon, then mix.
Spoon over tops of rolls.
Set pan in cold oven overnight.
Do not open oven door the next morning, but turn oven to 325° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Flip over onto plate while warm.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, mangoes, nuts and raisins.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening and baking powder into crumbs. Keep 1 small cup of crumbs for top of cakes.
Then add eggs, buttermilk with soda and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 4 cakes
done in old fashioned tins.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake for 15 minutes.

title: almond apricot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium saucepan combine nectar and apricots; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and cool.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
In separate bowl beat together egg and almond extract; stir in apricot mixture.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until moist. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full with batter. Sprinkle almonds over top of each cup.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: sunday sandwich
directions: Spread mayo on each slice of bread; add cheese slice and top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put top slice of bread on; beat egg with milk and pour it onto a large plate.
Dip both sides of sandwich into egg mixture; cook both sides on buttered grill until cheese melts.
Serve with relish.

title: nutty dessert
directions: Mix flour and oleo.
Add pecans, mix well and pat in oblong cake pan.
Bake about 25 minutes at 325° or until light brown. Cool completely.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add butter in as pie crust.
Mix egg yolks and milk; stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites. Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Arrange apples in rows on top. Mix topping mix and sprinkle on apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup in saucepan until it reaches 250°.
Pour over stiff beaten egg whites.
Beat until mixture loses gloss.
Roll onto buttered Reynolds Wrap.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up and cut with thread.

title: sugarless strawberry shortcake(not an old-fashioned recipe, but one in demand!)
directions: Clean and halve strawberries.
Combine with sugar substitute and water.
Toss gently to coat berries.
Refrigerate berries at least 2 hours.
Split biscuits and ladle half of your 3/4 cup serving of berries over bottom half of biscuit.
Ladle rest of serving portion over it.
Garnish each serving with a dollop of yogurt.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in crushed pineapple gradually, 1 cup of pecans and green pepper.
Refrigerate a few hours for easier handling.
Shape into ball.
Roll in the additional pecans.
Wrap in plastic, then foil. Refrigerate until well chilled, overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: clinton (president) chippers
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then peanut butter.
Add bananas last.
Bake for 16 to 18 minutes at 250°.

title: baked fish and vegetables
directions: Place fish in iron skillet with margarine. Season fish lightly with TexJoy steak seasoning); sprinkle parsley flakes over fish. Peel and slice potatoes and carrots (use amount desired) around and over fish. Place sliced onion and bell pepper over all and sprinkle with more parsley flakes. Cover and bake at 400° until potatoes and carrots are done. Mighty good!

title: leftover fish puffs
directions: Mix fish with cream cheese, onion, garlic and grated cheese. In a separate bowl, mix water and cornstarch to make a sealing paste.
Fill each egg roll wrapper with an appropriate amount of the fish and cheese mixture and fold over, sealing with the cornstarch paste.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken cutlets into cubes; saute until browned in oil. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread broccoli in bottom of pan.
Spread chicken over broccoli.
Combine cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top; dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: chuckwagon baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fry bacon and put aside.
Cook beef, onions and celery until vegetables are tender and meat is brown. Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Stir into meat and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut carrots into pieces.
Microwave until soft.
Mash them with a fork.
Let cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon over.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350°.
Bake another 50 minutes.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add 2 cups milk and cook slowly over low heat until slightly thickened.
Cool.

Add whipping cream, remaining 2 cups milk, vanilla and peaches, which have been sweetened with 1 cup sugar. Pour into a 4-quart container of electric or hand-turned freezer and freeze according to directions.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and garlic in a small saucepan and mix well. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring continually until thickened, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in black pepper.

title: quick and easy cake
directions: Place strawberries in bowl.
Add sugar; mix well and let set for 20 to 30 minutes to sweeten berries.
Mix cream cheese and margarine together with mixer.
Gradually add box of sugar while mixing with mixer.
Add just enough milk to make easy to spread on cake.
Mix in flavoring.
Take knife and make holes in top of cake, about every 2 inches.
Put tablespoon of strawberry mixture in holes.
Cover entire cake with icing.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: hazel dodson's sugar cookies
directions: Mix
oleo
and	sugar together well.
Add eggs and mix, then add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake at 375°.
Do not brown.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Microwave margarine in large mixing bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows; stir to combine. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 45 seconds.
Immediately add Rice Krispies cereal; stir until well coated.
Press mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in casserole and top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: beef marinade
directions: Blend well and refrigerate overnight with meat.
Will marinate 1 1/2 pounds of meat.
Let stand for 30 minutes at room temperature before cooking.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease bottom of pan with margarine.
Sprinkle rice in pan. Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Then reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 to 40 minutes more.

title: chocolate pot cake
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl with first ingredients.
Use spoon.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: four layer pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix first 4 ingredients together and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.

title: red pepper and broccoli pasta
directions: Peel and dice onion.
Saute in olive oil 10 minutes.
Cut pepper lengthwise; core and seed.
Cut in half width-wise, then julienne.
Add to sauteed onion along with garlic and red pepper flakes.
Continue to saute slowly 10 to 15 minutes, taking care not to burn garlic.

title: 6 layer bars(microwave)
directions: Layer in order of ingredients.
Cook in microwave 5 to 6 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter flavor shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla. Blend in egg.
Mix flour, salt and soda. Add to previous mixture. Stir in chips and nuts. Bake 8 to 10 minutes (for chewy cookies) or 11 to 13 minutes (for crispy cookies) at 375°.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process at liquefy until smooth.
Chill before serving.
Yields 2 cups.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix.
Add 1/3 cup to cup of hot water for Hot Cocoa.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Stir in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased loaf pan.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix egg yolks and milk; pour into dry ingredients.
Stir in butter and apples.
Fold in egg whites. Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased griddle.
Makes 12 medium pancakes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Beat well and add flour, dry ingredients and spices alternating with warm water just until smooth.
Drop by Tbsp. 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light and add rum flavoring. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add cocoa to flour and baking powder and sift.
Add
this
to
oleo
mixture,
a
little at a time, alternating, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour in greased, floured and brown papered tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°
or
until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: savory pea casserole
directions: Drain water chestnuts, reserving liquid.
Blend liquid with soup.
Saute onion, celery and gren pepper in butter in a skillet. Stir into this mixture, peas, pimiento and soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 12 or more servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker pie crust. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Yield: 2 pies.

title: zucchini provolone bake
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until just hot, not smoking.
Add onion and zucchini and cook 5 minutes or until zucchini is crisp-tender, stirring often.
Remove from heat; stir in basil, salt and pepper.
Add cheeses and eggs; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: almond broccoli chicken
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Add garlic, seasonings, and wine. Add chicken and cook until chicken turns white.
Add broccoli and continue to stir until it softens.
Add cream and reduce heat slightly until cream begins to thicken.
Add fettucini and 3/4 of cheeses; toss lightly.
Serve topped with remaining cheeses and almonds.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: You can use 1 pint of each vegetable; do not drain.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello and puddings in the water.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Cool.
When cool, fold in the Cool Whip and oranges.

title: martha's company casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add tomato sauce to meat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and pepper.
In buttered 2 quart casserole, spread 1/2 noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Pour on melted butter, then meat mixture.
Heat 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans; press into a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (approximately 30 minutes).
Cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt. Blend until crumbly the next 5 ingredients.
Spread over apples. Pour water over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salvation soup(low-fat)
directions: Bring water to boil and add bouillon cubes and vegetables. Cook about 10 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add tomato juice and drained green beans.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot.

title: pink lady
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Blend together eggs and oil. Add to dry ingredients. Then mixing with your hands, add in apples and nuts. Pour into tube or Bundt cake pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour plus 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Blend together sugar, vanilla, butter and eggs.
Combine 1 cup flour and baking powder and mix with egg mixture.
Blend fruit and nuts with 1/4 cup flour so fruits and nuts are coated with flour. Pour batter over floured fruits and nuts and blend.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° about 60 to 65 minutes.

title: "gooey" chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in greased Bundt pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, pumpkin and salad oil.
Beat.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices together.
Add to the first mixture.
Add nuts and pie filling last and beat well.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend in melted butter.
Press 2/3 of mixture into a lightly buttered 8-inch square cake pan. Cover with pie filling.
Sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool.
Cut into squares; serve topped with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes one 8-inch square.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mince 3 packages of ham and place in mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese, mustard, Miracle Whip and minced onion.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Roll the ball in the 4th package of minced ham and chill.

title: five can chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until nicely browned).

title: henry ford estate reuben bake
directions: Place cooked noodles in 13 x 9-inch pan and toss with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Top with sauerkraut.
In separate bowl mix crumbled corned beef with mayo.
Spread over sauerkraut. Layer with tomato slices and cover with all the shredded cheese. Top with crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: purple passion salad
directions: Mix and freeze in 9 x 13 in. dish.

title: grandma's fudge
directions: Heat the first four ingredients to boiling in a 5-quart pan. Boil 5 minutes with constant stirring. Remove from heat. Immediately add next three ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Pour into oiled cookie sheet. Store refrigerated or frozen.

title: sugar cookies(merle clarke's)
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Continue to add rest of ingredients and cream as added.
Dilute soda, water and vinegar before adding.
Drop batter from teaspoon and use back of another spoon (may have to use flour occasionally to keep from sticking) to flatten down on cookie sheet (greased).
Before baking, sprinkle with white sugar.
At Christmas time, use red and green sprinkles.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool before boxing.

title: mandarin yams
directions: Drain yams, reserving liquid.
Arrange first 3 ingredients in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Pour reserved liquid over all.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 17th century meat pie
directions: Mix meat and spices; refrigerate overnight.
Simmer meat with beef stock until all liquid has boiled away, 3 to 4 hours.
After meat has cooled, fill pie crusts and bake.
You can use beef for moose meat.
You can add grated carrot and celery; top with mashed potatoes before baking.

title: potluck beans
directions: Combine beans and onion in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in smoked sausage slices.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until beans are heated thoroughly, 10 to 15 minutes.
Use 350° setting on an electric skillet.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Brown first three ingredients in large skillet.
Cook spinach using directions; drain reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Add spinach liquid and next 5 ingredients to meat mixture. Simmer 20 minutes.
Combine spinach with pasta and remaining ingredients.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken-potato casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with layer of potatoes; slice butter over potatoes.
Brown chicken or pork chops, etc.
Lay over potatoes; cover with soup.
Bake, covered, at 250° until potatoes are tender.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine apples and 1 teaspoon lemon juice in large bowl.
Toss gently.
Add celery, grapes, nuts and raisins.
Toss gently; set aside.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter on low heat and add powdered sugar.
Stir together.
Roll into small balls.
Cool in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate bark.
Dip balls in chocolate bark with toothpick.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: emily's easy barbecue sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine soup, Worcestershire, vinegar, sugar and onion.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 10 minutes.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups sauce.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions.
Using a 13 x 9-inch pan, after removing cake from oven, immediately poke holes in the top of the cake.
Stir cream of coconut and cover entire top while cake is hot.
Let it cool completely.
Spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle top with coconut.
Cover tightly and put in a refrigerator and chill.
This is better made the day before you serve it.
Freezes nicely.

title: mama's pancakes
directions: Sift flour, measure and resift with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl, add milk and mix.
Stir in shortening; then add flour mixture all at once.
Beat until smooth.
Have griddle heated moderately hot.
Grease lightly. Pour out 1/4 cup batter for each cake.
Leave until top side is full of air bubbles and underside is brown, then turn and brown.

title: pickle sandwiches
directions: Drain pickles.
Cut crust from bread.
Mix onion, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice.
Spread mix on bread.
Roll pickles into bread, jelly-roll style.
Chill a couple of hours, then slice. Brown bread must be used!

title: russian pudding
directions: Mix flour and margarine.
Add pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups milk.
Spread on cheese mixture.
Mix chocolate pudding with 2 cups milk.
Spread on vanilla pudding.
Put the rest of the Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: quickly made kolache
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to combine all the ingredients.
Knead well.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/4-inch thickness and cut into 3-inch squares.
Fill with either poppy seed or crushed walnuts.
Pinch two opposite ends together. Lay folded side down on greased tin.
Or, instead of cutting into squares, spread poppy seed or walnuts across dough and roll like jelly roll.
Cut into slices.
Bake immediately at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: You will need a casserole (glass) dish.

title: sloe gin slush
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Let cool.
Add orange juice, lemonade, sloe gin and 2 cups cold water.
Put in freezer.
Stir occasionally until slushy.
Spoon into a glass and pour 7-Up over it.
Enjoy!

title: double quick dinner rolls
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well until smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise in warm place until doubles (about 30 minutes).
Grease 12 large muffin cups. Stir down raised dough.
Spoon into muffin cups, filling 1/2 full. Let rise again until double (20 to 30 minutes).
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Preparation time:
1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: In a large deep pan or pot add water, margarine, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Then add cabbage.
Steam until tender. Mix well to prevent burning.

title: maple syrup
directions: Bring sugar, water and brown sugar to boil.
Add maple, vanilla and butter extract.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Enjoy.

title: mom's stroganoff
directions: Cook beef chunks until tender; keep juice.
Add noodles; cook until tender.
Add soup and cream cheese.
The stuffed fettucine makes a so-so dish into a deluxe main course!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon into pie crust.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs and vanilla.
Form into balls and refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler, adding paraffin to thin. Dip balls, using a toothpick or fork.
Drop on wax paper.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: ky corn pudding
directions: Blend all but butter and mix well.
Butter baking dish and cut up butter in dish.
Pour mixture into center of dish and bake at 325°.
Stir 2 times during first 15 minutes and continue baking 30 more minutes.

title: cheap hot chili
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Slice jalapeno peppers and mix with chili powder and red pepper.
Drain baked beans.
Heat beans and chili sauce and add mixture.
Cook 1 cup of rice.
Mix cooked rice and chili mixture together.
Will feed 8.

title: dilled wilted cucumber
directions: Slice cucumbers thin and layer in large bowl with salt; set aside.
Stir together sugar, dill weed, lemon juice, water and pepper sauce.
Drain cukes well.
Add dressing and toss.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue creaming.
Add mashed bananas.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Add extract.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish (about 8 x 12 x 2) with chipped beef. Arrange chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all.
Refrigerate.

title: picante sauce
directions: Chop one onion and tomatoes in blender.
Empty into a big pot and simmer 1 hour stirring frequently.
Add sweetener, jalapeno peppers and other onion chopped.
You may can this in canning jars or serve cold.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together; best if worked by hand.
Shape into balls and brown well in skillet with hot oil.
Do about a dozen at a time.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice.
Add pecans and pineapple.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour. Makes 1 pie.

title: green tomato cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake in large baking pan.

title: mound cake
directions: Night Before:
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut well; refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, cook cake in 2 layers.
When cool, split layers, making 4.
Put mixture from refrigerator over each layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: double-decker chocolate pie
directions: To make crust:
Melt margarine.
Pour in Pyrex pan; cool and add flour and nuts.
Stir in.
Press down with fork.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: mrs betty's clam dip
directions: Drain clams and mix all ingredients together in top of double boiler. Heat and serve with chips or crackers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine corn flakes and margarine. Sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Cube bread; cut crust off first.
Place 1/2 of bread cubes into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased casserole dish.
Cube cream cheese and place on top of bread.
Beat eggs and combine with syrup and milk.
Pour egg and milk mixture over bread and cream cheese. Place rest of bread on top.
Place plastic wrap over casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: speedy clam chowder
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Cook chopped onion in same pan until tender.
Stir in potato soup, minced clams and milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 5 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Stir in bacon. Sprinkle with paprika and serve.
Serves 3.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Cover tightly and refrigerate. Keeps well.
Yields 2 cups.
Delicious with celery sticks, cucumbers, raw carrots, squash, cauliflower, broccoli or any vegetable which can be served as finger food.

title: microwave green beans with bacon dressing
directions: Microcook bacon at High 4 minutes, or until crisp.
Set aside; reserve 3 tablespoons drippings.
In small deep bowl, beat eggs with vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Add drippings; microcook at High, uncovered, 3 minutes or until thickened, beating with wire whisk twice during cooking.
(Sauce will curdle if not whipped vigorously.)
Place drained beans in casserole; cover and microcook at High 2 minutes, or until hot.
Arrange in serving dish; top with dressing.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: old-fashioned waldorf salad
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise, sugar, and lemon juice.
Toss with other ingredients; chill.

title: simple green bean casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 250°.

title: pepperoni caesar salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients and toss with Caesar Dressing.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries in baked pie shell.
Bring sugar, cornstarch and water to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Add strawberry jello and chill.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.

title: minted fruit punch
directions: Cook sugar and water to boiling point.
Pour over the mint leaves (10 or more leaves).
Simmer for 10 minutes; strain and chill.
Place block of ice in large punch bowl.
Over ice pour mint syrup, pineapple juice, orange juice, creme de menthe and lemon juice; stir to mix.
Just before serving, add carbonated beverage; stir lightly.
Garnish with lemon and lime slices.

title: uncooked fudge candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water in a double broiler.

title: mini bagels
directions: Stir together water and yeast in large bowl of electric mixer; let stand 5 minutes to soften yeast.
Stir in sugar and salt. Gradually mix in 4 cups of the flour and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
With a spoon stir in about 1 1/4 cups more flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth, elastic and no longer sticky (about 15 minutes).
Add more flour as needed to prevent sticking.
(Dough should be firm.)
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise in warm place until almost doubled (about 40 minutes).
Punch dough down and divide into thirds.
Set 2/3 of dough aside on floured board; cover with clear plastic film. Form remaining dough into a log and cut into 16 equal pieces.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Place cranberries, apples and sugar in a greased casserole. Mix flour, pecans and oatmeal and sprinkle over fruit.
Melt together margarine and orange juice.
Pour over the top of casserole mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown and bubbly.
Very good served with a pork roast.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Cook celery, carrots and scallions until tender, but not brown.
Add potato soup, broth, water and parsley. Cook and stir until boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes. Stir occasionally. Stir in cheese and cream.
Heat through.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer 1:
Avocados, lemon juice and salt (process in food processor until smooth).

title: hot dog goulash
directions: Saute hot dog slices in 1 tablespoon margarine until brown. Mix all ingredients together in a large pan and simmer until seasonings have a chance to permeate (10 minutes or so).
Add milk if mixture is too dry.

title: santa fe stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in a large pan.
Sprinkle dry taco seasoning, dry Ranch salad dressing, seasoning, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add remaining ingredients, including liquid. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: jake's fried fish
directions: Put fish sticks or fillets in vinegar, heat oil.
Remove fish from vinegar and drop in paper bag with meal, salt and pepper. Fry in hot oil until golden brown and floats to top of oil.

title: chili beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and minced onion. Add tomato and chili beef soup. Bring to simmer, stirring well. Blend in salt and chili powder. Line a 2-quart casserole with half corn chips. Spoon in meat mixture. Place remaining corn chips on meat layer. Sprinkle with
shredded cheese. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: lentil and brown rice soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In a large, heavy pot combine all but the last 3 ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat, cover the pot and simmer.
Cook for 45 to 55 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until the rice and lentils are both tender.
Remove and discard the bay leaf.
Stir in parsley, vinegar, salt and pepper.
If necessary, thin the soup with hot water.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Melt butter and chocolate over hot water.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, beating well.
Beat in chocolate and vanilla.
Mix in flour; stir in nuts. Spread into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Place all ingredients in pan; boil 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour sauce in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Add eggs. Add flour and fold in the rest of the ingredients. Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, making sure to mix well.

title: creamy ham and potato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on Medium (50%) for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese just begins to melt.
Stir occasionally.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sugar free chocolate frosting
directions: Blend together skim milk, vanilla and dream whip; beat until stiff.
Add pudding mix and continue to beat until light and fluffy.
Add more milk if too thick.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Pour zucchini, onions, salt and peppers in pan and let stand overnight or 3 to 4 hours.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Bring this to a boil, then add zucchini, peppers and onions.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Place in sterilized jars at once.
You may process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: les' harvest stuffing
directions: Saute first six ingredients in butter.
In bowl combine apples, nuts, raisins and herb stuffing mix.
Stir in sauteed vegies and butter until coated.
Mix in 3 loaves bread, which have been dried and cubed, until coated.
Combine juice and broth, then sparingly pour over stuffing until all is damp.
Stuffs 20 pound turkey and more!

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Skin and debone chicken.
Mix cheese and onion ends.
Place cream cheese balls in strip of chicken.
Place strip of bacon around chicken and secure with toothpicks.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Turn every 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole except the butter and corn flakes.
Place the corn flakes over the top of the casserole, then put the butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with vegetables(from my sister, pauline)
directions: Skin
chicken
breasts
and
dredge
in flour, salt and pepper.
Place
aluminum
foil
in
large baking pan.
Rub oil under
foil.
Add chicken to pan.
Sprinkle carrots and celery over chicken.
Mix wine and canned soup and pour over chicken. Sprinkle
soup mix over top and seal very tight.
Bake at 350° for 1
hours.
Serve
with rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings. This is a great dish for company.

title: souffle au chocolat (from moustache cafe)
directions: Using the 2 tablespoons of butter, coat the inside of 6 individual souffle dishes.
Sprinkle in the 2 tablespoons of granulated sugar to coat the inside.
Shake out the excess sugar. Make a roux by melting 1/2 cup of butter in a saucepan; add the flour, stirring constantly.
Set aside.
Place the milk and chocolate in another saucepan; stir constantly over low heat until chocolate melts.
Add the chocolate mixture to the roux.
Heat for 1 minute while stirring.
Remove mixture from heat and add the yolks.
Mix well using spatula; set aside.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mash cooked carrots and allow to cool.
Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add carrots, flour, nuts, egg, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Shape into walnut size balls and flatten slightly before placing on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet to cooling rack with waxed paper
or larger pan beneath.
Ice with glaze of orange juice and powdered sugar while cookies are hot.
Garnish with grated orange rind if desired.

title: pecan burgers
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon of butter, Worcestershire sauce and lemon pepper.
Heat until butter melts.
Add pecans and remove from heat.
Stir pecans into sauce until the sauce is absorbed.
Mix pecans with hamburger.
Shape into 10 patties.
Broil or grill burgers.
Sprinkle cheese on top of patty when almost done.
Serve on heated bun.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Make into small balls and put on cookie sheet.
Bake for 35 minutes at 300°.
When done, roll in powdered sugar and allow to cool.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Fry bacon slightly.
Peel potatoes and cut up; put in pot with bacon and cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are tender, then add cauliflower and cook until tender.
When all is done, mash mixture, leaving water.
Add enough milk to make soupy; salt and pepper to taste.

title: oyster sauce chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour and fry.
Mix other ingredients; boil together to make sauce.
Pour sauce over fried chicken and garnish with chopped green onions.

title: meaty stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes. Prick with fork.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let cool.
When cool enough to handle, slice off tops of potatoes.
Spoon out center, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Mash the potato centers.

title: barbecue for a crowd
directions: Brown meat with onions, pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until well seasoned.

title: chix chop chop casserole
directions: Combine all with half of onions.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: non fail pie crust
directions: Mix all together until it forms medium to small crumb balls. Put into storage containers.
When you are ready to use, take out as much as you need and just add enough water to form a mixture. Roll out on floured surface.

title: almond topped carrots
directions: In a saucepan, bring carrots and water to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes or until crisp but tender. Drain and add the raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice, ginger and pepper.
Place in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until the carrots are tender.
Sprinkle with almonds before serving.
Serves about 12.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: With a spoon, soften butter, gradually creaming in the sugar and vanilla.
Next, sift together the flour and salt.
Add walnuts to flour.
Combine flour and butter mixtures.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Roll in hands to 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Mix vinegar and seeds.
Pour over potatoes and sprinkle sugar over
and
chill.
When
cool, add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
I make a frozen ring of Kool-Aid and put in bowl to keep cool.

title: chicken a'la king
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir mushrooms and green peppers in butter for 5 minutes. Blend in salt, pepper and flour. Cook over low heat, stirring until bubbly.

title: russian cream makarova
directions: Blend sugar and gelatin; add water and mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes, then bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Pour in sweet cream and stir.
Mix sour cream with vanilla in medium size bowl.
Gradually beat in hot mixture. Pour into mold, serving bowl or individual pot de cremes.
Let cool.
Cover and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold with care. Serve with fresh berries.

title: dad's birthday cake
directions: Melt oleo and brown sugar in a pan.
Pour into pan and arrange pineapple slices, cherries and nuts on top of mixture.

title: nutty chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour, milk, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.
Add Nestle chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by 1/2 tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix all together and put in a bowl.
Chill for 1 hour.
Real fast.

title: white nut loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, Crisco and egg.
Stir in milk.
Add flour and blend well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until wooden toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak pinto beans in water for about 1 hour, then rinse. Place all ingredients in a crock-pot and cover with water.
Cook on high for about 6 to 7 hours or until beans are tender.
Add more water if needed; stir occasionally.
Serve with hot corn bread and fried potatoes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Morbus Sabbaticus or Sunday Sickness is a disease peculiar to church members.
The attack comes on suddenly on Sundays.
No symptoms are felt on Saturday night.
The patient sleeps well, awakes feeling well and eats a hearty breakfast.
But about church time, the attack comes on and continues until services are over for the morning.
Then the patient usually feels better by noon and is able to function normally the rest of the day.
None of the symptoms return until the next Sunday.
The peculiar features are as follows: spread until all family members are affected.

title: elisabeth sansom's baked creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth slowly and mix well.
Add soup and soup can of milk.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.

title: hard christmas candy
directions: In a large saucepan on medium heat cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until temperature is 310° (about 1/2 hour).
Remove from heat.
Add 1 bottle Loring Flavor oil of your choice and red or green food coloring.
Line a cookie sheet with foil and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Pour mixture onto cookie sheet and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Let cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight containers.
Try 1/2 of boiled mixture with 1/2 bottle cinnamon and red coloring.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Crush cookies in zipper-style bag with rolling pin.
Mix cookie crumbs with butter.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9 inch pie plate.
Pour in filling.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand 1/2 hour before serving so pie can be easily cut.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly in a glass loaf dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at power level High for 18 to 22 1/2 minutes, or until center is no longer pink.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli salad and dressing
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese and bacon in bowl.
Chill.
Mix mayo, sugar and lemon juice in bowl.
Chill.
Pour dressing over broccoli mixture just before serving.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture in bowl.
Top with vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat twice.
Chill thoroughly.

title: creamed poke salad
directions: Wash the poke salad good and cook until tender.
Drain well. Add cooked sauce to poke salad.
Eggs can be added to cooked poke salad.
A thin white sauce can be used.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 9 x 10-inch spring-form pan.
Mix flour and 3/4 cup of sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
To remaining mixture add baking powder, soda, salt, sour cream, 1 egg and almond extract.
Blend mixture together.
Spread batter over bottom and 2 inches up sides of pan.
In small bowl, mix cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg.
Pour over batter in pan; spoon preserves carefully over cheese filling.
In small bowl, mix 1 cup crumb mixture and sliced almonds.
Sprinkle over top; bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate leftovers.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease loaf pan or 8x8-inch square pan.
Mix all cake ingredients in a large bowl and spread in pan. Sprinkle topping mixture (see below) on top of batter and bake for 20-25 minutes.

title: rosy rhubarb cake
directions: Cut the first 5 ingredients together like pie crust.
Add the egg and milk; mix together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Top with the rhubarb.
Sprinkle with the jello.
Mix the soft butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup flour.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
In a separate pan, mix together Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Mix Knox gelatine and Jell-O together.

title: collard greens
directions: Pick greens, removing foreign objects, stems and yellow leaves.
Chop greens into small pieces and place in pot with salted chipped ham and ham hocks that have been cooking for about 1 hour.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let greens cook until tender (about two hours).
Yields 6 servings.

title: creamy french dressing for a crowd
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy, about 4 minutes. Add spices, then catsup and mayonnaise.
Continue to beat until very creamy.
Add oil slowly while continuing to mix. Add vinegar and water last; continue to beat for at least 5 minutes more.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat together sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, eggs, salt, vanilla and cinnamon; mix until soupy.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together flour, brown sugar, pecans and butter.
Spread over potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until topping is almost hard.

title: pineapple-banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Do not use mixer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Season with chicken breast with salt and pepper.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place 1/2 slice of cheese over each chicken breast.
Pour soup over chicken.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Pour butter over it.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or a little longer.

title: shrimp filled mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms, reserving 1/2.
Chop reserved stems and saute with onion in butter.
Add shrimp, Blue cheese and basil, mixing well.
Stuff mushroom caps with shrimp mixture and broil 5 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Serves 8.

title: apple pudding
directions: Pare, core and grate apples.
