Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Add apples, matzo meal, lemon rind and juice and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into greased deep ovenproof dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt over low heat, margarine.
Remove from heat, add brown sugar, and stir until blended.
Set aside to cool. Once cooled, stir in eggs. In a seperate bowl, sift flour, baking powder, & salt.
Add & blend to sugar mixture.
Add nuts & vanilla.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool & cut into squares.

title: working girl butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
To store, keep tightly sealed in refrigerator.

title: potato and corn cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes, corn, carrots and onion in 2 cups of boiling wter for about 10 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart pan.
Add garlic and onion; cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and both milks. Cook to heat, about 25 minutes.
Blend to puree in batches until all mixture is done.
Add spices; heat and serve.

title: easy vegetarian chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Simmer on low 4 to 6 hours.
Garnish with grated cheese and sour cream, if desired.

title: meatball stew
directions: Season ground beef to your taste.
Make small meatballs. Brown in large pot in small amount of oil.
Drain grease from meatballs when brown.
Add carrots, green peppers and onions.
Add enough water to pot to cover ingredients.
Cook over slow flame until carrots are tender (about 1 hour).
Add tomatoes and cook another 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts;
remove from bone. Combine celery and chicken soup.
Add
melted margarine.
Combine with dressing; add chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: fiesta corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet cook beef and drain. Add onion and peppers and cook until tender.
Set aside.
In large bowl mix meal, sugar, salt, baking powder, oil, eggs and milk.
Mix with meat.
Pour half in a greased 9 x 16-inch pan.
Cover with cheese slices.
Pour remaining mixture over cheese.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine egg and milk.
In a shallow dish, combine crackers, thyme, paprika and pepper; set aside.
Skin chicken.
Rinse and pat dry with paper towels.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in cracker mixture.

title: tuna souffle
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
When blended, add milk.
Cook until creamy sauce forms; stir constantly.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes in moderate oven.
Unmold and surround with cream eggs.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash.
Drain.
Place squash in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Make a paste of flour and soft margarine. Add to hot milk to form a thick paste.
Pour over squash and cheese.
Top with stuffing.
Dot margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and soda together.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Beat all together.
Bake at 350°.
Test with toothpick.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain the minced clams thoroughly and combine with the soup mix and sour cream.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours before serving.
Great with a vegetable tray.

title: creme of parisienne vegetable soup
directions: Cook frozen vegetables and carrots in water just until tender. Melt butter and margarine; add celery and onions.
Saute until onions are slightly clear.
Add flour; stir until well blended. Crush bouillon cubes and add 6 cups milk.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Add cooked vegetables plus the liquid.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium bowl on High for 45 seconds; stir.
(It will be partially melted.) Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Pour 2 cups milk in large bowl; add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping and spoon onto crust.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Thoroughly cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, soda, salt and buttermilk, mixing until smooth.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix and prepare in 2 layers and each layer split while warm.

title: elvis' favorite hamburgers
directions: Lightly mix all together with fork.
Make 4 thick burgers, handling as little as possible.
Grill over charcoal or on electric grill (can be broiled or fried, but grilled was always first choice).
Turn only once.
Do not flatten, as this will remove juices.
Serve on buttered toasted split buns.
Was served with Pepsi.

title: hot fruit bake
directions: Layer fruit in a 2-quart casserole dish and set aside.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; stir into butter.
Gradually stir in orange juice.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Pour hot mixture over lime jello. Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and pineapple.
Whip in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: sam's super bowl sausage
directions: Steam sausage; place in center of a lasagne pan in rows. Alternate around the outer edge potatoes, onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over all and place thinly sliced cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pheasant and wild rice
directions: Mix rice, canned soups, water and mushrooms in baking dish casserole.
Add browned pheasant.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over. Cover lightly with foil.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: pizza butter
directions: In bowl mix together.
Spread on English muffins and broil until light brown.

title: no bake chocolate-peanut drops
directions: In
large
bowl, stir together Kellogg's Frosted Flakes cereal and peanuts.
Place peanut butter morsels and chocolate morsels in
a
small microwave bowl.
Heat on High 2 minutes, stirring 1/2
way
through.
Stir morsels until smooth.
Pour melted morsels over cereal and peanuts, stirring until cereal and peanuts are coated.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet lined with
wax
paper.
Chill
until
set,
approximately 15 minutes. Store
at
room
temperature.
Per
serving:
100 calories. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: frosted cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Cut off stem leaving cauliflower whole.
Put water in a deep 1 1/2
quart
microwavesafe casserole.
Add cauliflower, stem
side down;
cover
with
lid
or
vented
plastic
wrap. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn once, just until cauliflower is tender.
Do not overcook.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and eggs to heat just enough to melt Jell-O.
Put Jell-O in.
Chill milk.
Freeze to icy in ice tray. Whip milk, then fold in other two ingredients.
Makes two pies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil together.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Gradually add the dry ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: In a nonstick frypan, add oil and all other ingredients.
Cook on low heat until all ingredients are tender.
Good with broiled hamburgers.

title: juice knox blox
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in saucepan.
Stir on low heat until completely dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in juice.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and chill.
Cut in squares or use cookie cutter and make shapes.
Can be held in fingers to eat.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish. In medium-size bowl, beat egg with small amount of water. In another bowl, combine potato flakes and salad dressing mix. Remove skin from chicken breasts (salt if desired). Dip chicken in egg and roll in potato flake mixture. Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake for an additional 30 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: citrus ambrosia
directions: *Dip apples and bananas in lemon juice or mix 1 tablespoon Fruit-Fresh with 1 quart of water to keep fruit from turning brown.
Bananas and kiwi fruits should be ripe but firm.

title: sausage grits
directions: Cook sausage until browned in a heavy skillet.
Drain well. Spoon into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine hot grits, cheese and butter.
Stir until cheese and butter melt.

title: french ham and cheese souffle
directions: Layer bread, ham and cheeses in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, mix flour, mustard, butter, eggs, cream, milk, 1 can of soup, hot sauce, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over ingredients in baking pan.
Chill 12 to 24 hours.
Spoon second can of soup on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with baked apple or other fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix up and refrigerate a few hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove from bone.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Combine chicken soup, cream of celery soup, onion, celery and milk; mix well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over top of mixture.
Pour 1 1/2 cups broth from chicken over stuffing.
Cut 1 stick butter into pats and put over top of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: gold cake
directions: Grease thoroughly and dust with flour a 10 x 14-inch sheet cake pan or a 10-inch tube pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Barely cover chicken with water.
With lid on, simmer until tender.
Drain the liquid and save for later use.
Bone the chicken.
Saute one small onion, minced in 3 tablespoons butter, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add 2 cups broth.
Bring to a boil slowly.
Add 1 cup frozen mixed vegetables or any vegetable you prefer.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup (undiluted) and chicken.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all, adding cheese and peppers last.
Bake in greased iron skillet for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cheese enchiladas
directions: In small bowl, combine soup and milk. Set aside. In medium bowl, combine chicken, salsa, chilies, chili powder, and 2 tablespoons of soup mixture. To make enchiladas, along one side of tortilla, spread about 1/3 cup chicken mixture. Roll up each tortilla, jelly-roll fashion; place seam-side down in greased 3 quart oblong baking dish or 9 x 13 pan. Spread remaining soup mixture over enchiladas. Cover with foil. Bake at 375 for 35 minutes or until bubbly. Top with shredded cheese, sour cream, olives, and green onions. Yield: 8 enchiladas.

title: sausage bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown sausage and onions.
Combine all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix in sausage, onions and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat 3 egg yolks and sugar until fluffy.
Add the flour until smooth.
Stir in the milk.
Cook until thickened slightly, stirring constantly.
Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Fold into cooked custard.
Don't let boil over.
Add flavoring of choice.
Top custard with nutmeg.

title: hot baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, onion, celery and peppers.
Mix cream with mayonnaise, salt, pepper, lemon juice and pecans.
Toss with chicken.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake 15 minutes or until light brown at 450°.
Serves 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Lightly grease and flour a loaf pan.
In
bowl, cream butter on high speed, gradually adding sugar, until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas and mix until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir just to moisten. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, pepper and sugar.
Set aside.
Heat vinegar enough to melt sugar.
Add salt and celery seed.
Pour over cucumbers and pepper and put in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Stir often.
Remove from refrigerator; put in containers and freeze.

title: easy skillet potatoes and ham
directions: You may use any amount of ingredients, depending on how many you want to serve.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown ground beef and add 1 package taco seasoning.
Place on top of cream cheese.
Next add green chilies.
Spread Cheddar cheese evenly on top of green chilies.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.
You can place in microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with tortillas.

title: crystal's seafood gumbo
directions: First make a roux.
Heat the oil in a large, heavy skillet. Slowly add the flour and whisk continually for 4 minutes, until the roux turns dark red.
Add the onions, bell peppers and celery.
Cook the vegetables until soft.
Stir in the seasonings and cook for 2 minutes, until well blended.
Remove from heat.

title: orange amrosia jello(serves 6)
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Add jello and cold water.
Chill until very thick.
Fold in cheese, nuts and Dream Whip.
Chill until firm.
This can be set in an ordinary bowl or a pretty mold.

title: danish finger sticks
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into shape of fingers.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: beef-cheese crescent pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt and salt.
Line pie pan with Pillsbury crescent rolls.
Mix slightly beaten egg with Cheddar or Colby cheese.
Spread cheese mixture over crust, then spread meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle with 8 ounce package Mozzarella (shredded).
Sprinkle top with paprika and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: raisin and honey scones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut butter into flour and salt until it resembles bread crumbs.
Add raisins, honey and milk.
Mix into a soft dough and turn out onto floured board and shape flat and round.
Cut into four sections and place on greased baking sheet. Brush top with a little milk.
Bake near the top of a hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Can be eaten as is or with butter and jam.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Mix together sugar, milk, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Then add flour mixture. Blend well. Pour batter into 8-inch round cake pan, greased. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise 1 hour.
Handle lightly; make into rolls.
Bake in a hot oven.

title: whipped potatoes
directions: Lay thawed hash browns in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Salt and pepper. Spread cream over the potatoes.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma ann's albondigas soup
directions: Form into small meatballs.
Place in pan.
Pour tomatoes and vegetables.
Place into Soup.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 325°.
Continue baking for 50 minutes.

title: grandma's date balls
directions: Cook 5 minutes, stirring while cooking over medium heat. While mixture is cooking, add nuts.
Remove from heat.
Pour in Rice Krispies and stir.
Let cool somewhat.
Form into balls. Roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Cut onion and pepper in thin rings; mix with cool carrots and put in all other ingredients. Pour over vegetables; cover and marinate 12 hours.
Keeps for 2 weeks.
Great for reunions, summertime and I like to put them on top of my spinach salad.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Then add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown beef in heavy pan.
Add all remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Add one tomato can of water.
Reduce and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: apples 'n cream pancake
directions: Combine milk, eggs, flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Heat heavy ovenproof 9-inch skillet in 450° oven until very hot.
Add butter to coat skillet; pour in batter immediately.
Bake on lowest oven rack at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Continue baking 10 minutes or until golden brown. Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Add sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Fill pancake with 3/4 cup cream cheese mixture; cover with apples.
Top with remaining cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Cut into wedges.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour a 5x9x3-inch loaf pan or 2 (4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) pans.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into pan(s). Bake 55 to 65 minutes at 350 degrees, or until tests done.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Fry bacon, save drippings.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add egg, butter and milk to dry ingredients.
Then add corn, chilies and bacon to mixture.
Mix.
Batter should be stiff. Add 2 tablespoons bacon drippings to skillet, then heat for 1 minute.
Add mixture to skillet and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet over medium heat; drain off fat. Using a fork, crumble cooked beef into pea-size pieces. In large pot, combine beef plus remaining ingredients. Bring to simmer over low heat and cook, stirring every 15 minutes, for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Stir in flour, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for 2 minutes until vegetables are coated and bubbly.
Stir in chicken broth, potatoes and carrots.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add milk; cook until almost boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in cheese; stir until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add garlic, oregano, soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread some sauce in shallow roasting pan (10 1/2 x 15-inch).
Arrange 4 alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread out rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix other ingredients together with mixer until smooth.
Spread over dough.
Top with favorite vegetables: broccoli, cauliflower, cherry tomatoes, onion, green pepper, cucumber, squash, celery, carrots, radishes and bacon bits.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes (45 minutes); drain water and mash potatoes with fork or potato masher in a 13 x 9 x 5-inch casserole dish.
Place dabs of butter over potatoes.
Add in sour cream. Add onions.
Add cheese.
Mix all ingredients well and place in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top of potatoes should bubble and brown when done.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, orange slices and juice, on medium speed with mixer, for 4 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: wonton
directions: Mix beef or pork, green onions, salt, shrimp and sugar.
Make small meatballs and cover with wonton.
Boil wonton in water for 10 minutes and take out.
Cook chicken soup, water and wontons together.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together into a bowl.
Blend cooking oil and butter.
Cut in with pastry blender until well blended. Sprinkle water over mixture and form into a ball, press firmly. Roll out dough between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Peel off paper. Use for pastry.

title: chicken with broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly done and place in bottom of buttered casserole.
Place boiled chicken on top.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, salt, curry powder and sherry.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, flour and milk, a little at a time, until all are added.
Add baking powder and flavorings.
Continue to mix a few minutes longer.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until done.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip slices into beaten eggs, then into bread crumbs.
Slowly heat oil in large frypan.
Saute eggplant until lightly browned; drain on paper towel.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a casserole dish (11 x 7-inch) starting with eggplant layer as follows:
eggplant, Ricotta or cottage cheese, sauce, Mozzarella cheese, seasoning and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat once.
Bake, uncovered, for approximately 20 minutes.

title: chocolate swirl cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla, salt and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour half mixture into crust. Drizzle 3/4 cup melted chocolate chips on top.
Mix with knife to swirl.
Pour over half mixture on top and drizzle remaining chocolate chips and swirl again.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool.
Chill 3 hours.

title: russian tea with pineapple
directions: Mix orange breakfast drink, tea, sugar, gelatin, cinnamon and cloves.
Store in a tightly closed container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons of the mix in each cup and fill with boiling water.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with the brown sugar.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Arrange pie sliced apples on top of the mixture.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour batter over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Invert cake when warm.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Blend together peanut butter, honey, evaporated milk, raisins and graham cracker crumbs.
Form logs by rolling out teaspoons of mixture on waxed paper.
Place logs on cookie sheets and chill for one hour.

title: chocolate-chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a mixer bowl; mix until smooth. Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots and slice in rounds. Cook in salted water until barely tender. Add onion and pepper.
Pour sauce over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mash 1/2 cup blueberries and stir into mixture.
Carefully stir in the rest of the blueberries whole.
Grease muffin pans and top surface of pans. Fill 2/3 full; sprinkle with sugar and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Add pumpkin to dry ingredients, along with 2 teaspoons baking soda, dissolved in 2 teaspoons milk.
Mix well.
Stir in 2 cups chocolate chips and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tuna mornay crepes
directions: Combine ingredients and cook crepes in crepe pan or frying pan sprayed with Pam.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar. Continue beating and gradually add sugar mixed with cornstarch. Beat until peaks form. Cover pie with meringue, taking extra care to seal off all edges. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: apricot bread
directions: Drain apricots, reserving syrup.
Puree apricots in blender. Add enough syrup to puree to measure 1 cup.
Sift together flour, powder, soda and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in orange juice and apricot puree. Add flour mixture and mix well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: egg casserole
directions: In small bowl, combine bacon, eggs, milk and onion.
Set aside.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles and place in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form a crust.
Place cheese slices over dough.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown and knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
To reheat, wrap loosely in foil and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil and mix in eggs, vanilla and zucchini. Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together, along with mashed bananas and nuts.
Mix well by hand and put into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: bombay salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve on lettuce and tomato salad.

title: black bean soup
directions: Cook beans in water. Cover and simmer (add salt) until most of the water is soaked up. Add stock and continue to cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours more.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In bowl, beat egg yolks, milk and lime juice.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with applesauce to butter mixture.
Add nuts and dates.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade tabbouleh
directions: Place the wheat in a large bowl or pan and pour in the boiling water.
Let soak for about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain the wheat and combine with the other ingredients, except the lettuce leaves.
Chill.
Heap salad on a plate and arrange the romaine leaves around the sides, so they can be used as scoops.

title: neapolitan ice cream pie
directions: Place chocolate ice cream in bottom of crust.
Chill until firm.
Spread strawberry ice cream over chocolate layer; chill until firm.
Top with vanilla ice cream and sprinkle top with toasted coconut.
Chill until firm.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir the margarine and salt in with spaghetti.
Beat eggs.
Add Parmesan cheese; mix with spaghetti. Place pasta mixture in 10-inch greased pie pan.
Shape like pie shell with spoon.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Pour meat mixture over cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
During the last 5 or 10 minutes, sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese; return to oven until melted.
Can be cut into pie shape pieces.

title: margaritas
directions: In a blender, combine tequila, Triple Sec, lime juice and crushed ice.
Blend until frothy.
Serve in a salt rimmed glass. Makes 4 servings.

title: breaded ranch chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the corn flakes, Parmesan cheese and salad mix.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in corn flake mixture to coat.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.
Yields 8 servings.

title: brownie mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in a cool place.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Layer in order listed. Serve with Tostitos.

title: bread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add salt, pepper, sage and poultry seasoning.
Add bread crumbs and cook until warm through. Add soup and stir until moistened.
Pour in casserole and bake at 400° for 15 to 30 minutes until hot.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage & macaroni casserole
directions: Cook sausage, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add flour and milk; stir until thick and cook macaroni.
Add macaroni to sauce. Add 1 c. of cheese and let melt.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with rest of cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on box.
Drain.
Make sauce of soup, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice and egg.
Layer baking dish with broccoli.
Cover with sauce and repeat layers.
Top with cheese and crackers.
Add melted butter on top if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese spread or dip
directions: *I like horseradish best for spread.
For dip sauce, use the sauce style.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost and squeeze out spinach.
Drain and cut up water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make and refrigerate the night before needed.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; then blend in remaining ingredients.
(For a softer cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.)
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry boy bait
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, baking powder, salt, butter, milk and eggs.
Blend at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 pan.
Arrange blueberries on top.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over the top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cut in squares and serve warm or cold.

title: egg-in-a-hole
directions: Cut hole in center of bread with a glass.
Melt margarine in pan.
Lightly brown bread slice on one side, then break egg in center.
Scramble egg slightly.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until egg is done and bread is brown on both sides.
Also brown the center piece that was cut out.
Served with bacon or sausage, this makes a quick, good breakfast.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into a loaf and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 35 minutes or until no longer pink in the middle and juices run clear.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick praline bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Arrange graham crackers in single layer in ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2

x 10 1/2 x 1 inch. Heat brown sugar and margarine to boiling in 2 qt. saucepan. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly; remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Pour sugar mixture over crackers; spread evenly. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly; cool slightly.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes; if skins are not good, peel.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish; fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with butter and herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned, cheese is melted and potatoes are soft inside.

title: fridge pickles
directions: Make a syrup with vinegar and sugar by bringing to a boil, reduce heat and stir for about 5 minutes at a gentle boil.
Add spices; pour over cucumbers, cover and store in fridge.
You will need enough sliced cucumbers to fill half of an ice cream bucket (gallon size).
These taste great!

title: corn and sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage and crumble.
Beat eggs in casserole.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in a little margarine until transparent and tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Crumble in saltine crackers. Add corn and milk (enough to make it soupy).
Add sausage and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: just-my-size pizzas
directions: *Items can be substituted or omitted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add to other ingredients. Chopped walnuts may also be added. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread with ground beef
directions: Brown meat and onions; add tomatoes.
Mix cornmeal, cream-style corn, salt, soda, eggs, grease and milk.
Heat iron skillet in oven.
Pour 1/2 cornmeal mixture into skillet, 1/2 meat and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat with second layer.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: skillet pork chops 'n rice
directions: Lightly saute onion and celery in oil.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper; add to skillet and brown on both sides.
Remove chops.
Add water, brown sugar, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce.
Stir and bring to boiling point.
Add rice and stir. (There will be a lot of liquid, but rice will absorb it.)
Return chops to skillet, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour on remaining tomato sauce, cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Top with a cup of buttered corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place crackers on a jelly roll pan or a large cookie sheet. In a saucepan, melt the 2 sticks of margarine.
Add 1 cup brown sugar and stir until smooth.
This takes at least 2 minutes.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour the mixture over the graham crackers.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix into hamburg 3/4 cup Italian bread crumbs, egg and salt. Mix well and form meatballs.
Place meatballs on cookie sheet and cook in 350° oven until meatballs are brown.
Remove from oven and simmer in tomato soup, brown sugar and vinegar for 30 minutes. Garnish with drained pineapple chunks.
